title: Low Loss 0.15dB LC/UPC to LC/UPC Single-mode Simplex Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | LSZH Jacket

title: Low Loss 0.15dB FC/APC to FC/UPC Single-mode Simplex Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | LSZH Jacket
descriptionHtml:
• Cable manufactured with industry-leading Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber, OS1/OS2 Compatible, durable high-quality simplex fiber optic connectors and industry standard flammability rating PVC 3.0mm simplex cable jacket
  • Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber is an ITU-T Recommendation G.652D compliant optical fiber with Corning’s enhanced low-loss and bend fiber technologies | This full-spectrum fiber has bend performance that exceeds the ITU-T Recommendation G.657.A1 standard and still splices the same as the installed base of standard Single-mode fibers such as SMF-28e+ fiber
  • SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber combines the benefit of industry-leading attenuation and improved macrobend performance, all in one fiber | This premium Single-mode fiber is designed for regional, long-haul, metro, access, mobile, and fiber to the home (FTTH) applications, along with being fully backward compatible with the installed base of legacy Single-mode fibers

title: Low Loss 0.15dB SC/APC to FC/UPC Single-mode Simplex Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | OFNR Jacket
descriptionHtml:
• Cable manufactured with industry-leading Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber, OS1/OS2 Compatible, durable high-quality simplex fiber optic connectors and industry standard flammability rating PVC 3.0mm simplex cable jacket
  • Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber is an ITU-T Recommendation G.652D compliant optical fiber with Corning’s enhanced low-loss and bend fiber technologies | This full-spectrum fiber has bend performance that exceeds the ITU-T Recommendation G.657.A1 standard and still splices the same as the installed base of standard Single-mode fibers such as SMF-28e+ fiber
  • SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber combines the benefit of industry-leading attenuation and improved macrobend performance, all in one fiber | This premium Single-mode fiber is designed for regional, long-haul, metro, access, mobile, and fiber to the home (FTTH) applications, along with being fully backward compatible with the installed base of legacy Single-mode fibers
  • High Quality Fiber Patch Cable for Storage Area Network and Data Networks and Connects to SFP Transceivers, Ethernet Switches and Media Converters

title: 0.2dB LC/APC to FC/UPC Single-mode Simplex Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | OFNR Jacket
descriptionHtml:
• Cable manufactured with industry-leading Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber, OS1/OS2 Compatible, durable high-quality simplex fiber optic connectors and industry standard flammability rating PVC 3.0mm simplex cable jacket
  • Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber is an ITU-T Recommendation G.652D compliant optical fiber with Corning’s enhanced low-loss and bend fiber technologies | This full-spectrum fiber has bend performance that exceeds the ITU-T Recommendation G.657.A1 standard and still splices the same as the installed base of standard Single-mode fibers such as SMF-28e+ fiber
  • SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber combines the benefit of industry-leading attenuation and improved macrobend performance, all in one fiber | This premium Single-mode fiber is designed for regional, long-haul, metro, access, mobile, and fiber to the home (FTTH) applications, along with being fully backward compatible with the installed base of legacy Single-mode fibers
  • High Quality Fiber Patch Cable for Storage Area Network and Data Networks and Connects to SFP Transceivers, Ethernet Switches and Media Converters

title: 0.2dB SC/UPC to SC/UPC Single-mode Duplex Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | LSZH Jacket
descriptionHtml:
• Cable manufactured with industry-leading Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber, OS1/OS2 Compatible, durable high-quality fiber optic connectors and industry standard flammability rating PVC 2.0mm zipcord cable jacket
  • Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber is an ITU-T Recommendation G.652D compliant optical fiber with Corning's enhanced low-loss and bend fiber technologies | This full-spectrum fiber has bend performance that exceeds the ITU-T Recommendation G.657.A1 standard and still splices the same as the installed base of standard Single-mode fibers such as SMF-28e+ fiber
  • SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber combines the benefit of industry-leading attenuation and improved macrobend performance, all in one fiber | This premium Single-mode fiber is designed for regional, long-haul, metro, access, mobile, and fiber to the home (FTTH) applications, along with being fully backward compatible with the installed base of legacy Single-mode fibers
  • High Quality Fiber Patch Cable for Storage Area Network and Data Networks and Connects to SFP Transceivers, Ethernet Switches and Media Converters
  • High Quality Guarantee: 100% Inspection and Test on Insertion Loss and Return Loss
  • Product SKU：SMDXRDSCUSCU2YZH

10GBASE-ER SFP+ Transceiver Module (SMF, 1550nm, 40km, Duplex LC, Industrial, DOM)

SFP+ transceiver supports up to 40km link lengths over SMF fiber. This transceiver is compliant with SFF-8432, 10GFC Rev 4.0 and 10GBASE-ER standards. Digital diagnostics monitoring is available via a 2-wire serial interface, as specified in SFF-8472.

Featuring an operating temperature range of -40°C to 85°C, this industrial fiber optic transceiver can work in harsh industrial environments, such as telecommunication, data processing & management, the application of industrial and factory automation, outdoor applications, rail and intelligent transportation systems (ITSs), marine, oil and gas, mining etc.

seo.description: SpeedyFiberTX 10GBASE-ER industrial SFP+ transceiver supports 40km over OS2 SMF via LC/UPC connector at 1550nm. With DOM, -40°C to 85°C temperature range, and compliance with SFF-8432 and 10GBASE-ER, it's ideal for telecom, automation, and outdoor networks.

title: 100GBASE-SR4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module, 850nm 100m MMF, DOM Monitoring, MPO-12/UPC Interface, Breakout to 4 × 25G-SR
descriptionHtml:
Cisco QSFP-100G-SR4-S Compatible 100GBASE-SR4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module (MMF, 850nm, 100m, MTP/MPO, DOM)

The Cisco QSFP-100G-SR4-S Compatible QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module is designed for use in 100GBASE Ethernet throughput up to 100m over OM4 multimode fiber (MMF) using a wavelength of 850nm via a MTP/MPO-12 connector. This transceiver is compliant with IEEE 802.3bm 100GBASE-SR4 and CAUI-4 standard. Digital diagnostics functions are also available via the I2C interface, as specified by the QSFP28 MSA, to allow access to real-time operating parameters. With these features, this easy to install, hot swappable transceiver is suitable to be used in various applications, such as data centers, high-performance computing networks, enterprise core and distribution layer applications.

seo.description: High-performance 100GBASE-SR4 QSFP28 optical transceiver module with 850nm VCSEL, up to 100m over OM4 MMF. MPO-12/UPC connector, breakout to 4×25G-SR, supports DOM via I2C. Ideal for data centers and high-speed networking.

title: 800GBASE 2 x SR4/SR8 OSFP Finned Top PAM4 850nm 50m DOM Dual MPO-12/APC MMF Ethernet Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
800GBASE-SR8 OSFP PAM4 Optical Transceiver Module (MMF, 850nm, 50m, Dual MTP/MPO-12 APC, DOM, Finned Top)

The 800GBASE-SR8 OSFP optical transceiver module is designed for 800GBASE Ethernet throughput up to 50m link lengths over OM4 multimode fiber (MMF) using a wavelength of 850nm via dual MTP/MPO-12 APC connectors. This transceiver is compliant with IEEE P802.3ck, OSFP MSA standards. The built-in digital diagnostics monitoring (DDM) allows access to real-time operating parameters.

The twin-port OSFP finned-top transceiver is used in Ethernet air-cooled switches. Featured with low latency, low power, and reliability, it can link upward in spine-leaf architectures for switch-to-switch applications, downward for top-of-rack switch links to Ethernet network adapters, and/or to BlueField-3 DPUs in compute servers and storage subsystems. It is the ideal solution for HPC computing, AI, and cloud data centers.

seo.description: 800GBASE-SR8 OSFP finned-top transceiver delivers 800Gbps over OM4 MMF up to 50m via dual MPO-12/APC connectors. Compliant with IEEE P802.3ck and OSFP MSA, it features low latency, DOM, and high reliability for spine-leaf, AI, and HPC data center networks.

title: 800GBASE 2 x DR4/DR8 OSFP Finned Top PAM4 1310nm 500m DOM Dual MPO-12/APC SMF Ethernet Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
800GBASE-DR8 OSFP PAM4 Optical Transceiver Module (SMF, 1310nm, 500m, Dual MTP/MPO-12 APC, DOM, Finned Top)

The 800GBASE-DR8 OSFP optical transceiver module is designed for 800GBASE Ethernet throughput up to 500m link lengths over OS2 single-mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1310nm via dual MTP/MPO-12 APC connectors. This transceiver is compliant with IEEE 802.3ck, IEEE 802.3cu and OSFP MSA standards. The built-in digital diagnostics monitoring (DDM) allows access to real-time operating parameters.

The twin-port OSFP finned-top transceiver is used in Ethernet air-cooled switches. Featured with low latency, low power, and reliability, it can link upward in spine-leaf architectures for switch-to-switch applications, downward for top-of-rack switch links to Ethernet network adapters, and/or to BlueField-3 DPUs in compute servers and storage subsystems. It is the ideal solution for HPC computing, AI, and cloud data centers.

seo.description: 800GBASE-DR8 OSFP finned-top transceiver delivers 800Gbps over OS2 SMF up to 500m via dual MPO-12/APC connectors at 1310nm. Compliant with IEEE 802.3ck/cu and OSFP MSA, it features DOM, low latency, and high reliability for AI, HPC, and spine-leaf networks.

title: 800GBASE-SR8 QSFP-DD PAM4 850nm 50M DOM MTP/MPO-16/APC MMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
800GBASE-SR8 QSFP-DD PAM4 Optical Transceiver Module (MMF, 850nm, 50m, MTP/MPO-16 APC, DOM)

The 800GBASE-SR8 QSFP-DD optical transceiver module is designed for 800G Ethernet applications and supports up to 50m transmission over OM4 multimode fiber (MMF) via MTP/MPO-16 APC connectors at 850nm wavelength. It complies with IEEE 802.3ck, CMIS 5.0, and QSFP-DD MSA standards.

With built-in digital diagnostics monitoring (DDM), this module enables access to real-time operating parameters for enhanced system management. It supports 2x 400G SR4 breakout configurations and is characterized by low latency, low power consumption, and high reliability—making it ideal for high-performance computing networks, data centers, enterprise core/distribution layers, and service provider infrastructures.

seo.description: SpeedyFiberTX 800GBASE-SR8 QSFP-DD transceiver delivers 800Gbps over OM4 MMF up to 50m via MTP/MPO-16 APC. With PAM4 modulation, DOM, and 2x400G breakout support, it’s ideal for high-performance computing, data centers, and low-latency networks.

title: 800GBASE 2 x 400G-XDR4/XDR8 QSFP-DD PAM4 1310nm 2km DOM Dual MPO-12/APC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
800GBASE-XDR8 QSFP-DD PAM4 Optical Transceiver Module (SMF, 1310nm, 2km, Dual MTP/MPO-12 APC, DOM)

The 800GBASE-XDR8 QSFP-DD optical transceiver module is designed for 800GBASE Ethernet throughput up to 2km link lengths over OS2 single-mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1310nm via dual MTP/MPO-12 APC connectors. This transceiver is compliant with IEEE P802.3ck, IEEE 802.3cu, QSFP-DD MSA standards. The built-in digital diagnostics monitoring (DDM) allows access to real-time operating parameters.

This module has 2x MPO-12 connectors, supports 2x 400G XDR4 and 8x 100G FR breakout applications. It can also be configured with a single port (4x 100G PAM4) for 400G applications. Featured with low latency, low power, and reliability, the product is suitable for 800G Ethernet, Data Center, high-performance computing networks, enterprise core and distribution layers, and service provider applications.

seo.description: SpeedyFiberTX 800GBASE QSFP-DD transceiver supports 2x 400G XDR4/XDR8 links over OS2 SMF up to 2km via dual MPO-12/APC connectors at 1310nm. With PAM4, DOM, and IEEE 802.3ck/cu compliance, it’s ideal for AI, HPC, and next-gen data center networks.

title: 2.5GBASE-T SFP to RJ45 Copper Transceiver, 100m Low-Power Module (LOS)
descriptionHtml:
2.5GBASE-T SFP Transceiver Module (Copper, 100m, RJ-45)

This 2.5GBASE-T SFP transceiver supports up to 100m link lengths over a copper connection via a RJ-45 connector. Each SFP transceiver module is individually tested to be used on a series of Generic switches, routers, servers, network interface card (NICs) etc. Featuring low power consumption and high speed, the 2.5G SFP transceiver is ideal for enterprise networking for LAN applications and different other networking places using copper connections.

seo.description: The 2.5GBASE-T SFP to RJ45 transceiver supports up to 100m over copper via an RJ-45 connector. Each module is individually tested for compatibility with switches, routers, servers, and NICs. With low power consumption and high-speed transmission, it is ideal for enterprise LAN applications and other copper-based networking environments.

title: 2.5GBASE-SX SFP Optical Transceiver, 850nm, 300m, Duplex LC, Multi-Mode Fiber (MMF), DOM
descriptionHtml:
2.5GBASE-SX SFP Optical Transceiver Module (MMF, 850nm, 300m, LC, DOM)

This 2.5GBASE-SX SFP transceiver supports up to 300m link lengths over multmode fiber (MMF) using a wavelength of 850nm via a LC connector. This transceiver is compliant with SFP MSA(INF-8074i), GR-253-CORE, ITU-T G.957, FC-PI v2.0 and SFF-8472 v9.5 standards. The built-in digital diagnostic monitoring (DDM) allows access to real-time operating parameters. It is suitable for SONET OC-48 SR-1/SDH STM-16 I-16, 2x Fibre Channel applications, switch to switch interface, switched backplane applications.

seo.description: 2.5GBASE-SX SFP Transceiver, 850nm, 300m, LC Duplex, Multimode Fiber (MMF), with Digital Diagnostics Monitoring (DOM). Designed for enterprise networks and data centers, compatible with Cisco, HPE, and MikroTik switches.

title: 2.5GBASE-T SFP Industrial Transceiver | 100m RJ-45 Copper Module with LOS
descriptionHtml:
2.5GBASE-T SFP Transceiver Module (Copper, 100m, Industrial, RJ-45)

This 2.5GBASE-T SFP transceiver supports up to 100m link lengths over a copper connection via a RJ-45 connector. Each SFP transceiver module is individually tested to be used on switches. Featuring low power consumption and high speed, the 2.5G SFP transceiver is ideal for enterprise networking for LAN applications and different other networking places using copper connections.

seo.description: 2.5GBASE-T SFP industrial transceiver, 100m RJ-45 Gigabit module with low-power design, ideal for switches, industrial networks, and data centers. Compatible with Cisco, HPE, and MikroTik switches for high-performance network transmission.

title: Ultra Low Loss 0.1dB LC/UPC to FC/UPC Single-mode Simplex Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | LSZH Jacket
descriptionHtml:

title: Ultra Low Loss 0.1dB SC/UPC to SC/UPC Single-mode Simplex Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | OFNR Jacket
descriptionHtml:
• Cable manufactured with industry-leading Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber, OS1/OS2 Compatible, durable high-quality simplex fiber optic connectors and industry standard flammability rating PVC 3.0mm simplex cable jacket
  • Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber is an ITU-T Recommendation G.652D compliant optical fiber with Corning’s enhanced low-loss and bend fiber technologies | This full-spectrum fiber has bend performance that exceeds the ITU-T Recommendation G.657.A1 standard and still splices the same as the installed base of standard Single-mode fibers such as SMF-28e+ fiber
  • SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber combines the benefit of industry-leading attenuation and improved macrobend performance, all in one fiber | This premium Single-mode fiber is designed for regional, long-haul, metro, access, mobile, and fiber to the home (FTTH) applications, along with being fully backward compatible with the installed base of legacy Single-mode fibers
  • High Quality Fiber Patch Cable for Storage Area Network and Data Networks and Connects to SFP Transceivers, Ethernet Switches and Media Converters
  • High Quality Guarantee: 100% Inspection and Test on Insertion Loss and Return Loss
  • Product SKU：SMSXUDSCUSCU3YNR

title: Ultra Low Loss 0.1dB LC/UPC to ST/UPC Single-mode Duplex Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | OFNP Jacket
descriptionHtml:
• Cable manufactured with industry-leading Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber, OS1/OS2 Compatible, durable high-quality fiber optic connectors and industry standard flammability rating PVC 2.0mm zipcord cable jacket
  • Corning SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber is an ITU-T Recommendation G.652D compliant optical fiber with Corning's enhanced low-loss and bend fiber technologies | This full-spectrum fiber has bend performance that exceeds the ITU-T Recommendation G.657.A1 standard and still splices the same as the installed base of standard Single-mode fibers such as SMF-28e+ fiber
  • SMF-28 Ultra Optical Fiber combines the benefit of industry-leading attenuation and improved macrobend performance, all in one fiber | This premium Single-mode fiber is designed for regional, long-haul, metro, access, mobile, and fiber to the home (FTTH) applications, along with being fully backward compatible with the installed base of legacy Single-mode fibers

title: 12-Fiber Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO/UPC to Non-Pinned MPO/UPC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM3 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type B, Aqua MPO Connectors, Aqua Cable Jacket | OFNR Jacket
descriptionHtml:
12-Fiber Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO/UPC to Non-Pinned MPO/UPC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM3 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type B, Aqua MPO Connectors, Aqua Cable Jacket | OFNR Jacket

This MPO to MPO jumper enables seamless migration to higher data rates when used with trunk cables, making it ideal for high-density fiber patching within cabinets. Featuring non-pinned UPC connectors with Type B polarity and built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM3 fiber, it offers low insertion loss, high return loss, and reliable performance. Pre-terminated for easy plug-and-play deployment, this cost-effective solution supports 40G/100G multimode transceivers in data center, FTTH, and EPON environments.

This MTP® to MTP® jumper enables seamless migration to higher data rates when used with trunk cables, making it ideal for high-density fiber patching within cabinets. Featuring non-pinned UPC connectors with Type B polarity and built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 fiber, it offers low insertion loss, high return loss, and reliable performance. Pre-terminated for easy plug-and-play deployment, this cost-effective solution supports 40G/100G multimode transceivers in data center, FTTH, and EPON environments.

title: Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO to 4xLC Duplex QSFP Type Breakout Cable | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Aqua MPO Connector, Aqua Cable Jacket, Beige LC Connectors | OFNR Jacket
descriptionHtml:
Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO to 4xLC Duplex QSFP Type Breakout Cable | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Aqua MPO Connector, Aqua Cable Jacket, Beige LC Connectors | OFNR Jacket

The MPO harnesses allow for the seamless migration to higher data rates in the data center when used in conjunction with our trunks. They are typically used for patching within a cabinet. MTP® cable, a cost-effective alternative to time-consuming field termination, is designed for high-density fiber patching in data centers which need space saving and reduce cable management troubles.

This low loss MPO to 4xLC Duplex QSFP Type breakout cable is designed for high-density fiber patching in data centers using multimode fiber systems. Built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 fiber, it supports 40GBASE-SR4 QSFP to 10GBASE-SR SFP+ breakout connections over short-reach multimode applications. The pre-terminated design ensures fast deployment and consistent low-loss performance.

Please note: The US Conec MTP® connectors are fully compliant with the MPO standards, which offer novel patented features, enhanced precision, proven reliability, and significant performance improvements compared to generic MPO connectors.

MTP® trunks are factory pre-terminated and rigorously tested to ensure stable performance in high-density cabling environments. Equipped with low-loss MTP® Elite connectors and SMF-28® Ultra single-mode fiber, these cables deliver excellent transmission quality across long-distance runs and multiple connection points. These features make MTP® trunks an ideal choice for high-density cabling in data centers, widely used in main, horizontal, and zone distribution areas.

Please note: The US Conec MTP® connectors are fully compliant with the MPO standards, which offer novel patented features, enhanced precision, proven reliability, and significant performance improvements compared to generic MPO connectors.

descriptionHtml:
Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO to 12xLC Breakout Cable | Corning® ClearCurve® OM3 Multimode Optical Fiber | Aqua MPO Connector, 900μm 12-Colored Hytrel® Fiber Tube, Beige LC Connectors

The MPO harnesses allow for the seamless migration to higher data rates in the data center when used in conjunction with our trunks. They are typically used for patching within a cabinet. MPO cable, a cost-effective alternative to time-consuming field termination, is designed for high-density fiber patching in data centers which need space saving and reduce cable management troubles.

This low loss MPO to 12xLC breakout harness is designed for high-density fiber patching in data centers. Built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM3 multimode fiber and a 900μm 12-colored Hytrel® tube, it simplifies cabinet patching and supports connections such as 40GBASE-SR4 to 10GBASE-SR via LC transceivers. The pre-terminated design ensures fast deployment and consistent low-loss performance.

Please note: The US Conec MTP® connectors are fully compliant with the MPO standards, which offer novel patented features, enhanced precision, proven reliability, and significant performance improvements compared to generic MPO connectors.

Elite Non-Pinned MTP® to 24xLC Breakout Cable | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Magenta MTP® Connector, 600μm 24-Colored Hytrel® Fiber Tube, Beige LC Connectors

The MTP® harnesses allow for the seamless migration to higher data rates in the data center when used in conjunction with our trunks. They are typically used for patching within a cabinet. MTP® cable, a cost-effective alternative to time-consuming field termination, is designed for high-density fiber patching in data centers which need space saving and reduce cable management troubles.

This Elite MTP® to 24xLC breakout cable is ideal for high-density multimode applications in data centers. Built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 fiber and a 600μm 24-colored Hytrel® tube, it supports 100GBASE-SR10, parallel optics, and structured cabling deployments. The pre-terminated design ensures fast deployment and consistent low-loss performance.

Please note: The US Conec MTP® connectors are fully compliant with the MPO standards, which offer novel patented features, enhanced precision, proven reliability, and significant performance improvements compared to generic MPO connectors.

title: Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO to 4xLC Duplex QSFP Type Breakout Cable | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Aqua MPO Connector, Aqua Cable Jacket, Beige LC Connectors | OFNP Jacket
descriptionHtml:
Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO to 4xLC Duplex QSFP Type Breakout Cable | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Aqua MPO Connector, Aqua Cable Jacket, Beige LC Connectors | OFNP Jacket

The MPO harnesses allow for the seamless migration to higher data rates in the data center when used in conjunction with our trunks. They are typically used for patching within a cabinet. MTP® cable, a cost-effective alternative to time-consuming field termination, is designed for high-density fiber patching in data centers which need space saving and reduce cable management troubles.

This low loss MPO to 4xLC Duplex QSFP Type breakout cable is designed for high-density fiber patching in data centers using multimode fiber systems. Built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 fiber, it supports 40GBASE-SR4 QSFP to 10GBASE-SR SFP+ breakout connections over short-reach multimode applications. The pre-terminated design ensures fast deployment and consistent low-loss performance.

Please note: The US Conec MTP® connectors are fully compliant with the MPO standards, which offer novel patented features, enhanced precision, proven reliability, and significant performance improvements compared to generic MPO connectors.

title: Audio-Optimized SFP Optical Transceiver｜1310nm Single-mode LC Duplex｜For Hi-Res Streaming Systems
descriptionHtml:
Audio-Optimized SFP Optical Transceiver｜1310nm Single-mode LC Duplex｜For Hi-Res Streaming Systems

The SpeedyFiberTX Audio-Optimized Special-Spec SFP transceiver is purpose-built for high-fidelity streaming environments. Supporting 1Gbps transmission (1000BASE-LX/LH), it delivers exceptional stability and low interference for Hi-Res audio applications. Internally fine-tuned and constructed with components selected for audio use, it ensures clean, uninterrupted signal transmission between NAS, Roon Core, Lumin, and DAC systems—resulting in a quiet, interference-free audio background during long listening sessions.

This module is equipped with DOM (Digital Optical Monitoring) functionality, allowing real-time monitoring of optical power, voltage, and temperature—giving users greater control and reliability during extended streaming playback. Compatible with most SFP-ready switches on the market, it is an ideal solution for home HiFi networks, professional audio environments, and demanding users seeking clean and stable digital transmission in their audio systems.

✅ Recommended Devices & Compatibility Notes
For best results, pair with the SpeedyFiberTX Single-mode LC/UPC Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra | Low Insertion Loss 0.1dB | Optimized for Hi-Res Audio Streaming (SMDXUDLCULCU2YNR). This combo has been field-tested in Hi-Fi setups to provide optimal signal integrity from NAS to DAC through audio-grade switches.
This module is compatible with most network switches equipped with SFP or SFP+ ports, and is ideal for high-resolution audio network setups—such as Roon Core, Lumin, audiophile-grade NAS, and DAC streaming systems. 


⚠️ Important Notes:
．Some common models such as Netgear GS105Ev2, GS108Ev3, and GS110TP (v1/v2) are RJ45-only and do not support SFP modules. Please confirm your switch has an SFP or SFP+ slot (SFP+ is backward-compatible with 1G SFP) before purchasing.

．This module is built to MSA standards and is Cisco-compatible, and functions reliably on most open-platform switches, including QNAP, MikroTik, TP-Link, Netgear, and others. It is not limited to Cisco equipment.

seo.description: SpeedyFiberTX audio-optimized SFP transceiver supports 1Gbps (1000BASE-LX/LH) single-mode fiber with LC/UPC connectors. Ideal for Hi-Res audio streaming with Roon Core, NAS, DAC, and Lumin. DOM-enabled for stable, low-noise long-distance transmission.

Easy-Pull Uniboot Low Loss 0.15dB OM4 LC/UPC to LC/UPC Fiber Patch Cable | Corning OM4 Fiber | Aqua Connector | OFNR Jacket | Speedy Model A Easy-Pull Uniboot

SpeedyFiberTX Uniboot Fiber Patch Cable designed with Easy-Pull tab, providing seamless access in ultra-dense patch panels—without the need for traditional pull tabs. It supports tool-free polarity reversal and delivers low loss performance.

Constructed with Corning OM4 fiber, it ensures consistent, high-speed signal transmission for enterprise networks, cloud infrastructure, and data center deployments. The compact uniboot design reduces cable volume and improves airflow, built with an OFNR-rated jacket suitable for vertical riser installations in commercial buildings.

This MTP® to MTP® jumper enables seamless migration to higher data rates when used with trunk cables, making it ideal for high-density fiber patching within cabinets. title: Low Power Consumption Gigabit Ethernet Compact Media Converter - TAA
descriptionHtml:
The Gigabit Fiber Media Converter converts standard RJ-45 Ethernet into high-performance optical signals. Designed with an SFP slot, it offers maximum flexibility to support a wide range of transceiver options—including SC, LC, BiDi, and WDM—depending on the module installed. This compact and reliable converter greatly extends transmission distances, making it an excellent choice for FTTH, apartment networks, and campus deployments.

Crafted in Taiwan, it reflects the precision and durability of a premium networking device. Unlike mass-produced alternatives, it delivers consistent quality that IT professionals and enthusiasts can trust.

✨ Audiophile Advantage

For discerning audio enthusiasts, fiber transmission provides natural electrical isolation, eliminating ground loops and reducing noise commonly introduced over copper Ethernet. This ensures a cleaner digital signal path, delivering a blacker background and more stable streaming performance. When paired with high-grade single-mode fiber and a low-noise linear power supply, it enhances detail, clarity, and musical presence—making it a refined addition to high-end audio systems.

title: SpeedyFiberTX Single-mode LC/UPC Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra | Low Insertion Loss 0.1dB | Optimized for Hi-Res Audio Streaming
descriptionHtml:
🔊 A Trusted Choice in the Audiophile Community

This single-mode LC/UPC to LC/UPC fiber patch cable by SpeedyFiberTX, featuring Corning® SMF-28® Ultra fiber, has become a popular upgrade option across audio forums in recent years.

Whether for two-channel streaming setups, digital streaming DACs, or high-end audio network switches, this cable integrates seamlessly.

Tested by audiophiles from Taiwan and around the world, it consistently delivers low noise, high signal clarity, and stable soundstage, even without special tuning or wrapping. It’s often regarded as the best price-performance option among entry-level single-mode optical cables.

Recommended Pairing

For best results, pair with the SpeedyFiberTX Audio-Optimized SFP Module (SFP1G-LX-31-AF). This combo has been field-tested in Hi-Fi setups to provide optimal signal integrity from NAS to DAC through audio-grade switches.

Easy-Pull Uniboot Low Loss 0.15dB OM3 LC/UPC to LC/UPC Fiber Patch Cable | Corning OM3 Fiber | OFNR Jacket | Speedy Model A Easy-Pull Uniboot

SpeedyFiberTX Uniboot Fiber Patch Cable designed with Easy-Pull tab, providing seamless access in ultra-dense patch panels—without the need for traditional pull tabs. It supports tool-free polarity reversal and delivers low loss performance.

Constructed with Corning OM3 fiber, it ensures consistent, high-speed signal transmission for enterprise networks, cloud infrastructure, and data center deployments. The compact uniboot design reduces cable volume and improves airflow, built with an OFNR-rated jacket suitable for vertical riser installations in commercial buildings.

title: 10GBASE-BX40-U BiDi  SFP+ 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX 40km DOM
descriptionHtml:
10GBASE-BX40 SFP+ Transceiver Module (SMF, 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX, 40km, LC,DOM)

SFP+ transceiver supports up to 40km over OS2 SMF via an LC simplex connector. This 10G BiDi SFP+ transceiver, featured with data transmission over a single strand of fiber, the one transceiver transmits a 1270-nm channel and receives a 1330-nm signal, whereas the other BiDi SFP+ optics transmits at a 1330-nm wavelength and receives a 1270-nm signal.

Digital diagnostics can also be used through the I2C interface designated by SFF-8472 to allow access to real-time operating parameters. Each BIDI SFP+ transceiver module is individually tested to be used on a series of switches, routers, servers, network interface cards (NICs) etc. Featuring low power consumption and high speed, this 10G BIDI SFP+ transceiver is ideal for enterprise wiring closets, service provider transport applications, Radio & Baseband Units, etc.

seo.description: 10GBASE-BX40 SFP+ BiDi transceiver module delivers 10Gbps over a single OS2 SMF strand up to 40km via LC simplex connector. One transceiver operates at 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX, the other at 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX. With DOM support and low power consumption, ideal for enterprise, telecom, RRU, and baseband applications.

title: 10GBASE BiDi SFP+ 1550nm-TX/1490nm-RX 80km DOM Simplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module (Industrial)
descriptionHtml:

This 10G BiDi SFP+ transceiver, featured with data transmission over a single strand of fiber, the one transceiver transmits a 1550-nm channel and receives a 1490-nm signal, whereas the other BiDi SFP+ optics transmits at a 1490-nm wavelength and receives a 1500-nm signal.

Featuring an operating temperature range of -40°C to 85°C, this industrial fiber optic transceiver can work in harsh industrial environments, such as telecommunication, data processing & management, the application of industrial and factory automation, outdoor applications, rail and intelligent transportation systems (ITSs), marine, oil and gas, mining etc.

title: 10/25GBASE-CSR SFP28 Dual-rate 850nm 400m DOM Duplex LC/UPC MMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
10/25GBASE-CSR SFP28 Optical Transceiver Module for Data Center ( MMF, 850nm, 400m, LC, DOM)

SFP28 transceiver provides 10/25GBase-CSR throughput up to 400m over multimode fiber (MMF) using a wavelength of 850nm via an LC duplex connector. This module provides 10G backward compatibility and simplifies network upgrade. It provides connectivity option for 25G Ethernet, 10G Ethernet and data center.

It is fully compliant with the SFF-8472, SFF-8024, SFF-8431 and IEEE802.3by standard. Featuring low power consumption and high speed, this 25G transceiver is ideal for 25G Ethernet, Telecom, and Data Center.

title: 1/10GBASE-LR SFP+ 1310nm 20km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module (Industrial)
descriptionHtml:
1/10GBASE-LR SFP+ Optical Transceiver Module (SMF, 1310nm, 20km, LC, DOM)

1/10GBASE-LR SFP+ transceiver supports up to 20km over OS2 SMF via an LC duplex connector.

This transceiver is compliant with IEEE802.3ae, SFF-8432, SFF-8431, 10GFC and FC-PI-4. Featuring low power consumption, high speed, this 10G SFP+ transceiver is ideal for data center, 10G Ethernet and Fibre Channel etc.

seo.description: This 1G/10GBASE-LR SFP+ transceiver supports 1310nm wavelength over OS2 single-mode fiber for distances up to 20km via LC duplex connector. Compliant with IEEE802.3ae and SFF standards, it features DOM support, low power, and high performance for Ethernet and Fibre Channel networks.

title: 10GBASE-BX10 BiDi SFP+ SMF Transceiver 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX & 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX 10km DOM Simplex LC/UPC
descriptionHtml:
1. SFP+ 10GBASE-BX10-D Transceiver Module (SMF, 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX, 10km, LC, DOM) ｜ 2. SFP+ 10GBASE-BX10-U Transceiver Module (SMF, 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX, 10km, LC, DOM)

This SFP+ transceiver supports up to 10km link lengths over OS2 SMF via an LC simplex connector.

This 10G BiDi SFP+ transceiver, featured with data transmission over a single strand of fiber, the one transceiver transmits a 1330-nm channel and receives a 1270-nm signal, whereas the other BiDi SFP+ optics transmits at a 1270-nm wavelength and receives a 1330-nm signal.

seo.description: 10GBASE-BX10 SFP+ BiDi transceiver module pair features single-mode fiber (SMF) LC simplex interface. One module transmits at 1270nm and receives at 1330nm, while the other transmits at 1330nm and receives at 1270nm. Supports up to 10km transmission with Digital Optical Monitoring (DOM). Ideal for ISP, enterprise LANs, and high-speed single-fiber data center applications.

title: 10GBASE-BXX-20km BiDi SFP+ SMF Transceiver 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX & 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX 20km DOM Simplex LC/UPC
descriptionHtml:
1. SFP+ 10GBASE-BX20-D Transceiver Module (SMF, 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX, 20km, LC, DOM) ｜ 2. SFP+ 10GBASE-BX20-U Transceiver Module (SMF, 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX, 20km, LC, DOM)

This SFP+ transceiver pair supports up to 20km link lengths over OS2 single-mode fiber (SMF) via LC simplex connectors. Designed for bidirectional data transmission over a single strand of fiber, one module transmits at 1330nm and receives at 1270nm, while the other transmits at 1270nm and receives at 1330nm.

Digital diagnostics monitoring (DOM) is available via the I2C interface defined in SFF-8472, allowing access to real-time operating parameters.

Each BiDi SFP+ module is individually tested for compatibility with switches, routers, servers, and network interface cards (NICs).With low power consumption and high-speed performance, this 10G BiDi SFP+ pair is ideal for enterprise wiring closets, service provider transport networks, and applications such as Radio and Baseband Units (BBUs).

seo.description: 10GBASE-BX20 SFP+ BiDi transceiver pair supports 20km transmission over OS2 SMF via LC simplex. One module transmits at 1330nm and receives at 1270nm, while the other transmits at 1270nm and receives at 1330nm. With DOM, low power, and high speed, they fit enterprise, telecom, and baseband applications.

title: 25GBASE-ESR SFP28 850nm 300m DOM Duplex LC/UPC MMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
25GBASE-ESR SFP28 Optical Transceiver Module (MMF, 850nm, 300m, LC, DOM)

SFP28 transceiver provides 25GBase-ESR throughput up to 300m over OM3 MMF (400m over OM4) using a wavelength of 850nm via a LC duplex connector. Besides, it offers interoperability, laying a foundation for the next-generation network upgrade. Each SFP28 transceiver module is individually tested in targeted switch, and is fully compliant with the SFP28 MSA, RoHS, SFF-8424, SFF-8431 and SFF-8432 standards.

Featuring low power consumption and high speed, this 25G transceiver is ideal for 25G Ethernet, Telecom, and Data Center.

seo.description: The 25GBASE-ESR SFP28 optical transceiver delivers up to 300m over OM3 and 400m over OM4 multimode fiber using an 850nm wavelength via LC duplex connectors. Fully compliant with SFP28 MSA standards, it features low power consumption and high-speed performance, making it ideal for 25G Ethernet, telecom, and data center applications.

title: 25GBASE-D SFP28 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX 10km DOM Simplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
25GBASE-BX10-D SFP28 Optical Transceiver Module for Data Center and Telecom (SMF, 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX, 10km, LC, DOM)

SFP28 transceiver provides 25GBase-BX throughput up to 10km over single mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX via an LC simplex connector.

This bidirectional unit must be used with another transceiver or network appliance of complimenting wavelengths. It provides 25GBASE Ethernet connectivity option for 25G Ethernet, telecom and data center. It is fully compliant with the SFP28 MSA, CPRI and eCPRI standard.

seo.description: The 25GBASE-BX10-D SFP28 optical transceiver supports up to 10km over single-mode fiber (SMF) via an LC simplex connector using 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX wavelengths. Designed for bidirectional transmission, it must be paired with a complementary wavelength unit. Fully compliant with SFP28 MSA, CPRI, and eCPRI standards, it is ideal for 25G Ethernet, telecom, and data center applications.

title: 25GBASE-LR SFP28 1310nm 10km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver
descriptionHtml:
25GBASE-LR SFP28 DOM Optical Transceiver Module for Data Center and Telecom (SMF, 1310nm, 10km, LC, DOM)

SFP28 transceiver provides 25GBase-LR throughput up to 10km over single mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1310nm via an LC duplex connector. The SFP28 transceiver works on the same 10G network cabling Infrastructure, boosting speed by at least 2.5 times. It also features DDM/DOM for real-time monitoring of operating status.

This hot-swappable transceiver is pre-programmed, uniquely serialized, and tested for data traffic and application performance. Besides, it offers interoperability, laying a foundation for the next-generation network upgrade. Each SFP28 transceiver module is individually tested in targeted switch, it is fully compliant with the SFP28 MSA, CPRI and eCPRI standard. Featuring low power consumption, high speed, this 25G transceiver is ideal for 25G Ethernet, telecom, and data center.

seo.description: 25GBASE-LR SFP28 transceiver supports up to 10km over single-mode fiber (SMF) using a 1310nm wavelength via an LC duplex connector. It features DDM/DOM for real-time monitoring, low power consumption, and high-speed performance. Fully compliant with SFP28 MSA, CPRI, and eCPRI standards, this hot-swappable module is ideal for 25G Ethernet, telecom, and data center applications.

title: 25GBASE-SR SFP28 850nm 100m DOM Duplex LC/UPC MMF Optical Transceiver
descriptionHtml:
25GBASE-SR SFP28 Optical Transceiver Module for Data Center and Telecom (MMF, 850nm, 100m, LC, DOM)

SFP28 transceiver adopts LC duplex connectors, reaching a link up to 100m over OM4 MMF (70m over OM3). The SFP28 transceiver module supports running on the same 1G/10G network cabling Infrastructure, giving 2.5 times increase in speed at least, and the built-in DDM/DOM functions monitor the real-time operating status.

This hot-swappable transceiver is pre-programmed, uniquely serialized, and tested for data traffic and application performance. Besides, it offers interoperability, laying a foundation for the next-generation network upgrade. Each SFP28 transceiver module is individually tested on a series of Cisco switches, and is fully compliant with the SFP28 MSA, RoHS, CPRI, and the eCPRI standards. Featuring low power consumption, high speed, this 25G transceiver is ideal for 25G Ethernet, telecom, and data center.

seo.description: 25GBASE-SR SFP28 transceiver supports up to 100m over OM4 multimode fiber (MMF) or 70m over OM3 using an 850nm wavelength via an LC duplex connector. It features DDM/DOM for real-time monitoring, low power consumption, and high-speed performance. Fully compliant with SFP28 MSA, RoHS, CPRI, and eCPRI standards, this hot-swappable module is ideal for 25G Ethernet, telecom, and data center applications.

title: 25GBASE-U SFP28 BiDi 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX 20km DOM Simplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
25GBASE SFP28 Optical Transceiver Module for Data Center and 5G Wireless Network (SMF, 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX, 20km, LC, DOM)

SFP28 transceiver provides up to 20km of 25GBase-BX throughput over single-mode fiber (SMF) using 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX wavelengths via LC simplex connectors.

This bi-directional unit must be used with another transceiver or network equipment of complementary wavelengths. It provides 25GBASE Ethernet connectivity options for 25G Ethernet, telecom, data center and 5G Network Fronthaul. It is fully compliant with SFF-8472, SFF-8402, SFF-8432, SFF-8431, MSA and eCPRI standards.

seo.description: 25GBASE-BX SFP28 transceiver supports 20km over SMF using 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX via simplex LC connector. Ideal for 25G Ethernet, telecom, data centers, and 5G fronthaul, it features DOM monitoring and complies with MSA, SFF, and eCPRI standards.

title: 25GBASE-U SFP28 BiDi 1270nm-TX/1330nm-RX 40km DOM Simplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
25GBASE-BX40-U SFP28 Optical Transceiver Module for Data Center and Telecom (SMF, 1270nm-TX/1310nm-RX, 40km, LC, Industrial, DOM)

SFP28 transceiver provides 25GBase-BX throughput up to 40km over single mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1270nm-TX/1310nm-RX via an LC simplex connector. This bidirectional unit must be used with another transceiver or network appliance of complimenting wavelengths.

It provides 25GBASE Ethernet connectivity option for 25G Ethernet, telecom and data center, suitable for both outdoor and indoor deployments. It is fully compliant with the SFP28 MSA, CPRI and eCPRI standard.

seo.description: The 25GBASE-BX40-U SFP28 optical transceiver supports up to 40km transmission over OS2 single-mode fiber via an LC simplex connector, using 1270nm-TX/1310nm-RX wavelengths. Designed for industrial-grade performance, it operates in harsh environments and is ideal for 25G Ethernet, telecom networks, and data center interconnections. Fully compliant with SFP28 MSA, CPRI, and eCPRI standards, it must be paired with a matching wavelength transceiver for proper bidirectional communication.

title: 25GBASE-D SFP28 BiDi 1330nm-TX/1270nm-RX 40km DOM Simplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
25GBASE-BX40-D SFP28 Optical Transceiver Module for Data Center and Telecom (SMF, 1310nm-TX/1270nm-RX, 40km, LC, Industrial, DOM)

SFP28 transceiver provides 25GBase-BX throughput up to 40km over single mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1310nm-TX/1270nm-RX via an LC simplex connector. This bidirectional unit must be used with another transceiver or network appliance of complimenting wavelengths.

It provides 25GBASE Ethernet connectivity option for 25G Ethernet, telecom and data center, suitable for both outdoor and indoor deployments. It is fully compliant with the SFP28 MSA, CPRI and eCPRI standard.

seo.description: 25GBASE-BX40-D SFP28 optical transceiver (SMF, 1310nm-TX/1270nm-RX, 40km, LC, Industrial, DOM) delivers high-speed 25GBase-BX connectivity over a single fiber strand, ideal for data center and telecom applications. Fully compliant with SFP28 MSA, CPRI, and eCPRI standards.

title: 10/25GBASE-LR SFP28 Dual-rate 1310nm 10km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module (Industrial)
descriptionHtml:
10/25GBASE-LR SFP28 Industrial Dual-rate Optical Transceiver Module for Data Center (SMF, 1310nm, 10km, DOM)

SFP28 transceiver provides 10/25GBASE-LR throughput up to 10km over single mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1310nm via an LC duplex connector. This module provides 10G backward compatibility and simplifies network upgrade.

It provides connectivity option for 25G Ethernet, 10G Ethernet telecom and data center, suitable for both outdoor and indoor deployments. It is fully compliant with the SFP28 MSA, SFF-8472, SFF-8402, SFF-8432 and applicable portions of SFF-8431 standard.

seo.description: 10/25GBASE-LR SFP28 industrial dual-rate optical transceiver (SMF, 1310nm, 10km, LC, DOM) supports both 10G and 25G transmission, offering low power consumption and high performance. Ideal for data center, telecom, and both indoor and outdoor deployments. Compliant with SFP28 MSA and multiple industry standards.

title: 40GBASE-LR4 QSFP+ 1310nm 10km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
40GBASE-LR4 QSFP+ Optical Transceiver Module (SMF, 1310nm, 10km, LC, DOM)

The QSFP+ module is designed for use in 40GBASE Ethernet throughput up to 10km over single mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1310nm via duplex LC connectors. This transceiver is compliant with QSFP+ MSA and IEEE 802.3ba 40GBASE-LR4 and OTU3 C4S1-2D1 standard.

Digital diagnostics functions are also available via the I2C interface, as specified by the QSFP+ MSA, to allow access to real-time operating parameters. With these features, this easy to install, hot swappable transceiver is suitable to be used in various applications, such as data centers, high-performance computing networks, enterprise core and distribution layer applications.

seo.description: High-performance 40GBASE-LR4 QSFP+ transceiver supports up to 10km over SMF via LC duplex connectors at 1310nm. Compliant with QSFP+ MSA and IEEE 802.3ba standards, with DOM support for real-time monitoring. Ideal for data centers, HPC networks, and enterprise core applications.

title: 40GBASE-SR4 QSFP+ 850nm 150m DOM MPO-12/UPC MMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:

The QSFP+ module adopts 12 Fibers MTP/MPO Male connectors, reaching a link up to 150m over OM4 MMF (100m over OM3). This transceiver is compliant with IEEE 802.3 40GBASE-SR4 standard. At the same time, it is completely interoperable with all standard 40GBASE-SR4 interfaces.

Digital diagnostics functions are also available via the I2C interface, as specified by the QSFP+ MSA, to allow access to real-time operating parameters. With its easy installation and hot-swappable design, this transceiver is ideal for various applications, including campus, data center, cloud deployments, high-performance computing environments, and interconnections between switches, routers, servers, and transport equipment.

seo.description: 40GBASE-SR4 QSFP+ transceiver supports up to 150m over OM4 MMF via MTP/MPO connectors at 850nm. Compliant with IEEE 802.3 40GBASE-SR4 standard, with DOM for real-time monitoring. Ideal for data centers, cloud, HPC, and high-speed interconnections.

title: 40GBASE-PLR4L QSFP+ 1310nm 2km DOM MPO-12/APC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
40GBASE-PLR4L QSFP+ Optical Transceiver Module (SMF, 1310nm, 2km, MTP/MPO, DOM)

The QSFP+ module is designed for use in 40GBASE Ethernet throughput up to 2km over single mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1310nm via a MTP/MPO-12 connector. This transceiver is compliant with 100G PSM4 MSA. Digital diagnostics functions are also available via the I2C interface, as specified by the 100G PSM4 MSA, to allow access to real-time operating parameters.

With these features, this easy to install, hot swappable transceiver is suitable to be used in various applications, such as data centers, high-performance computing networks, enterprise core and distribution layer applications

seo.description: 40GBASE-PLR4L QSFP+ transceiver supports up to 2km over SMF via MTP/MPO-12 connectors using 1310nm wavelength. Compliant with 100G PSM4 MSA, it features DOM monitoring, hot-swappable design, and is ideal for data centers, HPC, and enterprise core networks.

title: 25GBASE-LR SFP28 1310nm 10km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module for 5G Wireless (Industrial)
descriptionHtml:
25GBASE-LR SFP28 DOM Optical Transceiver Module for Data Center and 5G Wireless Front-haul (SMF, 1310nm, 10km, LC, Industrial, DOM)

25GBase-LR throughput up to 10km over single mode fiber (SMF) using a wavelength of 1310nm via an LC duplex connector.

Featuring low power consumption, high speed, this 25G transceiver is ideal for 25G Ethernet, and data center. Each SFP28 transceiver module is individually tested in targeted switch, it is fully compliant with the SFP28 MSA, CPRI and eCPRI standard.

seo.description: The 25GBASE-LR SFP28 optical transceiver supports 25Gbps up to 10km over OS2 single-mode fiber (SMF) via LC duplex connector using a 1310nm wavelength. With industrial-grade design, low power consumption, and DOM support, it is ideal for data center interconnects, 25G Ethernet, and 5G wireless front-haul applications.

title: 8-Fiber Elite Non-Pinned MTP®/APC to Non-Pinned MTP®/APC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type B, Green MTP®-12 Connectors, Aqua Cable Jacket | LSZH Jacket

This MTP® to MTP® jumper enables seamless migration to higher data rates when used with trunk cables, making it ideal for high-density fiber patching within cabinets. Featuring non-pinned APC connectors with Type B polarity and built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 fiber, it offers low insertion loss, high return loss, and reliable performance. Pre-terminated for easy plug-and-play deployment, this cost-effective solution supports 40G/100G multimode transceivers in data center, FTTH, and EPON environments.

Please note:The US Conec MTP® connectors are fully compliant with the MPO standards, which offer novel patented features, enhanced precision, proven reliability, and significant performance improvements compared to generic MPO connectors.

Each MTP®-12 connector is pre-loaded with 8 fibers in positions 1-4 and 9-12, following the standard 8-fiber configuration for parallel optical transmission.

12-Fiber Elite Pinned MTP®/APC to Pinned MTP®/APC Jumper | Corning® SMF-28® Ultra Single-mode Optical Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | Type A, Yellow MTP® Connectors, Yellow Cable Jacket | OFNR Jacket

This MTP® to MTP® jumper enables seamless migration to higher data rates when used with trunk cables, making it ideal for high-density single-mode fiber patching within cabinets and backbone networks. Featuring pinned APC connectors with Type A polarity and built with Corning® SMF-28® Ultra single-mode fiber, it ensures superior transmission performance with low insertion loss and high return loss. Pre-terminated for easy plug-and-play deployment, this cost-effective solution supports long-reach 40G/100G applications in data centers, FTTH, and and EPON environments.

Please note: The US Conec MTP® connectors are fully compliant with the MPO standards, which offer novel patented features, enhanced precision, proven reliability, and significant performance improvements compared to generic MPO connectors.

seo.description: The Elite Pinned MTP® to Pinned MTP® Jumper features Corning® SMF-28® Ultra Fiber with Type A polarity and a pre-terminated design for consistent low-loss performance. Featuring  yellow MTP® connectors and a yellow jacket, it supports high-density patching and long-reach 40GBASE-PLR4/100GBASE-PSM4 single-mode parallel optics in modern data centers.

title: 8-Fiber Elite Non-Pinned MTP®/UPC to Non-Pinned MTP®/UPC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type B, Magenta MTP®-12 Connectors, Aqua Cable Jacket | LSZH Jacket
descriptionHtml:
8-Fiber Elite Non-Pinned MTP®/UPC to Non-Pinned MTP®/UPC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type B, Magenta MTP®-12 Connectors, Aqua Cable Jacket | LSZH Jacket

This MTP® to MTP® jumper enables seamless migration to higher data rates when used with trunk cables, making it ideal for high-density fiber patching within cabinets. Featuring non-pinned UPC connectors with Type B polarity and built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 fiber, it offers low insertion loss, high return loss, and reliable performance. Pre-terminated for easy plug-and-play deployment, this cost-effective solution supports 40G/100G multimode transceivers in data center, FTTH, and EPON environments.

Please note:The US Conec MTP® connectors are fully compliant with the MPO standards, which offer novel patented features, enhanced precision, proven reliability, and significant performance improvements compared to generic MPO connectors.

Each MTP®-12 connector is pre-loaded with 8 fibers in positions 1-4 and 9-12, following the standard 8-fiber configuration for parallel optical transmission.

title: 12-Fiber Elite Pinned MTP®/UPC to Non-Pinned MTP®/UPC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type A, Magenta MTP® Connectors, Aqua Cable Jacket | LSZH Jacket
descriptionHtml:
12-Fiber Elite Pinned MTP®/UPC to Non-Pinned MTP®/UPC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type A, Magenta MTP® Connectors, Aqua Cable Jacket | LSZH Jacket

This MTP® to MTP® jumper enables seamless migration to higher data rates when used with trunk cables, making it ideal for high-density fiber patching within cabinets. Featuring non-pinned UPC connectors with Type A polarity and built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 fiber, it offers low insertion loss, high return loss, and reliable performance. Pre-terminated for easy plug-and-play deployment, this cost-effective solution supports 40G/100G multimode transceivers in data center, FTTH, and EPON environments.

Please note:The US Conec MTP® connectors are fully compliant with the MPO standards, which offer novel patented features, enhanced precision, proven reliability, and significant performance improvements compared to generic MPO connectors.

title: 8-Fiber Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO/APC to Non-Pinned MPO/APC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type B, Yellow MPO-12 Connectors, Magenta Cable Jacket | OFNP Jacket

This MPO to MPO jumper enables seamless migration to higher data rates when used with trunk cables, making it ideal for high-density fiber patching within cabinets. Featuring non-pinned APC connectors with Type B polarity and built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM4 fiber, it offers low insertion loss, high return loss, and reliable performance. Pre-terminated for easy plug-and-play deployment, this cost-effective solution supports 40G/100G multimode transceivers in data center, FTTH, and EPON environments.

Each MPO-12 connector is pre-loaded with 8 fibers in positions 1-4 and 9-12, following the standard 8-fiber configuration for parallel optical transmission.

title: MTP®/MPO Polarity Tester | Fast A/B/C Polarity & Fiber Fault Detection - TAA
descriptionHtml:
The MTP®/MPO Polarity Tester is an essential tool for engineers and technicians to verify the integrity of MTP®/MPO fiber optic cables and determine the A/B/C polarity of their connectors. It supports both single-mode (SM) and multi-mode (MM) cables, and is compatible with MTP/MPO input/output ports equipped with either physical contact (PC) or angled physical contact (APC) connectors.

By emitting a 650 nm visible red laser through the fiber optic cable, the tester can detect breaks and defects along the channel. When a break is present, the refracted light produces a bright glow at the fault location, while the display indicates the issue with the pattern “--”. In addition, the tester is equipped with 12 LEDs that clearly display the status of each 12F or 8F channel, making troubleshooting faster and more reliable.

The laser diode provides three output modes:

• Scan Mode – for testing MTP/MPO array and fan-out cables.

• Continuous Wave (CW) Mode – for continuous fan-out cable testing.

• Pulse Mode – for fan-out cable testing with pulsed light emissions.

seo.title: SpeedyFiberTX MTP/MPO Polarity Tester
seo.description: peedyFiberTX MTP/MPO Polarity Tester is a professional fiber optic tool for fast A/B/C polarity verification and fiber fault detection. It quickly checks MPO array and fan-out cables for polarity, integrity, and channel breaks, supporting both single-mode and multi-mode fibers with PC or APC connectors—an essential device for fiber maintenance and network reliability.

title: MTP®/MPO Tester Mini | Quick Test for 12/16/24F MPO/MTP Cables - TAA
descriptionHtml:
The MTP®/MPO Tester Mini is a compact and highly useful tool for detecting defects in MTP®/MPO array fiber cables or connectors. It emits a 650 nm visible red laser through fiber optic cables, and if breaks or defects are present, the light refracts to create a bright glow around the faulty area.

The LD output signal can switch across all 12F, 16F, or 24F fibers, operating in Continuous Wave (CW) mode or other modes to produce different visual effects for efficient testing and troubleshooting.

seo.title: SpeedyFiberTX MTP/MPO Tester mini
seo.description: SpeedyFiberTX MTP/MPO Tester Mini provides fast fiber fault detection with a 650nm red laser, visible up to 1 km. It supports 12/16/24F MTP/MPO array cables and delivers stable laser output with CW, Pulse, Scan Circular, and Manual modes. Powered by USB-C with an internal battery, it is a compact, cost-effective solution for fiber maintenance and MTP/MPO polarity testing.

title: Fiber Checker | 650nm Visual Fault Locator - TAA
descriptionHtml:
The Fiber Checker is a very useful tool designed for checking the defects of a fiber cable. It emits a visible 650 nm wavelength red laser light through fiber optic cables, then if there are breaks or defects in the fiber will refract the light, creating a bright glow around the faulty area.

The universal connector can be used for all the most widespread fiber interfaces such as ST / SC / FC connector. It is suitable to test both Singlemode and Multimode cables. With an optional 2.5 mm to 1.25 mm optional Adapter, you can easily test 1.25 mm diameter fiber LC or MU connector. The visibility is from 3 km to 5 km dependent upon the output power of the Fiber Checker.

Internally there is also a specifically designed power circuit called an APC (Auto Power Control) circuit which provides steady power. The APC prevents unstable laser output when the battery is low.

The LD output signal can be switched to CW or Pulse Mode to obtain different visual effects. There is a dust cap which will prevent dirt from getting into the LD connector. The cover also prevents accidental exposure of the laser beam into anyone’s eyes.
tags: ST SC FC LC MU connector

seo.title: SpeedyFiberTX Fiber Checker
seo.description: The Fiber Checker is a compact 650nm visual fault locator for fiber optic cables, supporting ST/SC/FC/LC/MU connectors, singlemode & multimode, with up to 5 km visibility and stable CW/Pulse modes.

title: Portable Light Source | Portable Multi-Wavelength Optical Tester
descriptionHtml:
Light Source is a handy instrument to provide you several wavelengths for testing the fiber equipment in an optical network and FTTx construction. Light Source is ideal for field or laboratory testing of optical communication systems at 850nm / 1300nm for datacom testing, 1310nm / 1550nm / CWDM 1270nm ~ 1610nm ( 20nm spans ) for all WDM testing , as well as 1490 nm for FTTx testing by changing the interchangeable SFP module. Light Source features zero warm up, superb productivity and is easy to use with its pocket-size and rugged handy design.

With a LC / SC patch cord, the Light Source can be used for most widespread fiber interfaces such as LC / ST / SC / FC connectors. It is suitable to test both Singlemode and Multimode cables.

Internally there is a specially designed power circuit called APC (Auto Power Control). The APC circuit provides continuous power which avoids unstable laser output when the battery is low.

The LD output signal can be switched between Continuous Wave (CW) or Pulse Mode 270Hz / 2KHz Modulated Mode to simulate signal transmission. There is a dust proof cap which will prevent dirt from getting into the LD connector. The cap also helps avoid accidental exposure to the laser beam into your eyes.

seo.title: SpeedyFiberTX Light Source
seo.description: The Light Source offers multiple wavelengths (850/1300/1310/1550 nm, CWDM 1270–1650 nm) for fiber testing, supporting singlemode & multimode cables. Compact, stable, and ideal for FTTH, WDM, CATV, and lab applications.

descriptionHtml:
The MTP®/MPO Tester is a very useful tool designed for checking the defects of MTP/MPO arrayed fiber cables or connectors. It emits a visible 650 nm red laser light through fiber optic cables. If there are breaks or defects in the fiber, the light will refract and create a bright glow around the faulty area.

The LD output signal can be switched for all 12, 16, or 24 fibers in CW Mode to obtain different visual effects.

seo.description: The MTP/MPO 12F/16F/24F Tester is a 650nm visual fault locator for MTP/MPO fiber cables and connectors, supporting CW/Pulse/Manual modes with stable output and up to 1 km visibility.

title: Power Meter | Optical Power Tester 850/1310/1490/1550nm - TAA
descriptionHtml:
The Power Meter is mainly used for checking the signal output power of the optical communication equipment in fiber optic networks. It measures the average power of a continuous light beam which is emitted from the equipment or other optic sources. It measures power both in 850 nm (Multimode) / 1310 nm / 1550 nm (Singlemode) and 1310 nm / 1490 nm / 1550 nm (Singlemode) respectively.

The Power Meter consists of a solid state InGaAs photo diode, signal power measurement circuitry, and a 3 Digits LED display. Users just connect a fiber cable between the transmission port of the equipment and the universal interface on the Power Meter or connect to other light source. The product will show the exact amount of the received power (in – xx.x dBm).

The universal connector can be used for all the most common fiber interfaces such as ST / SC / FC and it is suitable to test both Singlemode and Multimode cables. With an optical 2.5 mm to 1.25 mm adapter, users can even test for 1.25 mm fiber interface.

seo.title: SpeedyFiberTX Fiber Optic Power Meter | Optical Power Tester for 850/1310/1490/1550 nm
seo.description: The Fiber Optic Power Meter measures optical signal power at 850/1310/1490/1550 nm, supporting singlemode & multimode fibers with -40 dBm ~ +5 dBm range, 3-digit LED display, and universal connectors.

title: 10GBASE-ER SFP+ 1310nm 40km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
10GBASE-ER SFP+ Transceiver Module (SMF, 1310nm, 40km, LC, Industrial, DOM)

SFP+ transceiver supports up to 40km link lengths over OS2 SMF via an LC duplex connector. Digital diagnostics monitoring is available via a 2-wire serial interface, as specified in SFF-8472. Each SFP+ transceiver module is individually tested to be used on a series of Cisco switches, routers, servers, network interface card (NICs) etc. Featuring an operating temperature range of -40°C to 85°C, this industrial fiber optic transceiver can work in harsh industrial environments, such as telecommunication, data processing & management, the application of industrial and factory automation, outdoor applications, rail and intelligent transportation systems (ITSs), marine, oil and gas, mining etc.

seo.description: SpeedyFiberTX 10GBASE-ER SFP+ industrial transceiver supports 40km over OS2 SMF via LC/UPC duplex connector at 1310nm. With DOM and -40°C to 85°C wide temperature range, it's ideal for telecom, outdoor, and industrial automation applications.

descriptionHtml:
LC Duplex PVC Single-mode Fiber Loopback Module

The fiber loopback module is designed to provide a media of return patch for a fiber optic signal. Typically it is used for fiber optic testing applications or network restorations. For the testing applications, the loopback signal is used to diagnose a problem. Sending a loopback test to network equipment, one at a time, is a technique for isolating a problem.

Fiber loopback modules can provide an economical solution for many fiber optic test applications.

title: 10G SFP+ AOC
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX 10G SFP+ AOC

SFP+ Active Optical Cables are direct-attach fiber assemblies with SFP+ connectors and operate over Multi-Mode Fiber (MMF). This AOC is compliant with SFF-8431 MSA standards. It provides a cost-efficient solution as compared to using discrete optical transceivers and optical patch cables and is suitable for 10Gbps connections within racks and across adjacent racks.

The optics are completely contained inside the cable, which—without LC optical connectors to clean, scratch, or break—dramatically increases reliability and lowers maintenance costs. AOCs are most often used for creating 1-30m short switch-to-switch or switch-to-GPU links.

seo.description: 10G SFP+ Active Optical Cable (1m, SFP+ to SFP+, MMF) complies with SFF-8431 MSA standards and supports 10Gbps high-speed transmission. Ideal for data center rack-to-rack connections, eliminating optical connector cleaning and maintenance while ensuring high reliability and cost efficiency.

title: 56G QSFP+ AOC
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX 56G QSFP+ AOC

The Generic Compatible QSFP+ Active Optical Cables are direct-attach fiber assemblies with QSFP+ connectors and operate over Multi-Mode Fiber (MMF). This AOC is compliant with SFF-8436 MSA standards.

It provides a cost-efficient solution as compared to using discrete optical transceivers and optical patch cables and is suitable for 56Gbps connections within racks and across adjacent racks.

seo.description: The 56G QSFP+ Industrial Active Optical Cable (AOC) is a four-channel pluggable fiber assembly designed for short-range, high-speed interconnects in demanding environments. Operating over multimode fiber (MMF) at 850nm, it integrates four data lanes in each direction, supporting an aggregated 56Gbps bandwidth. Built with ruggedized industrial-grade design and compliant with SFF-8436 MSA standards, this AOC ensures reliable performance for data centers, telecom, and Infiniband FDR/EDR applications.

title: 100G QSFP28 AOC
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX 100G QSFP28 AOC

QSFP28 Active Optical Cables are fiber assemblies with QSFP28 connectors designed for direct-attach connections over Multi-Mode Fiber (MMF). These AOCs comply with hot-pluggable QSFP28 MSA and RoHS-6 standards, ensuring compatibility and adherence to environmental regulations.

By offering a cost-efficient alternative to discrete optical transceivers and patch cables, these AOCs are ideal for establishing 100Gbps connections within racks and adjacent racks. Active optical cables provide a lightweight and slim alternative to copper cables, simplifying cable management.

seo.description: The 100G QSFP28 Active Optical Cable (AOC) is a direct-attach fiber assembly with QSFP28 connectors, supporting 100Gbps connections up to 3 meters over multimode fiber (MMF). Fully compliant with QSFP28 MSA and RoHS-6 standards, this lightweight and hot-swappable AOC offers a cost-effective alternative to discrete transceivers and patch cables. Ideal for high-speed interconnects within racks and adjacent racks, it also simplifies cable management in data centers and enterprise networks.

title: 200G QSFP56 AOC
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX 200G QSFP56 AOC

The 200G QSFP56 Active Optical Cable (AOC) is designed for 200 Gigabit Ethernet links over OM3 or OM4 multimode fiber.

Each end integrates four transmit and four receive optical channels (full-duplex, 8 lanes in total), with each channel operating at up to 50 Gb/s PAM4, delivering an aggregated data rate of 200 Gb/s.

This AOC complies with IEEE 802.3cd, SFF-8665, SFF-8636, and QSFP56 MSA standards, providing a reliable, low-power, and high-density interconnect solution for modern data centers.

seo.description: The 200G QSFP56 Active Optical Cable (AOC) is a high-performance fiber assembly with QSFP56 connectors, supporting 200Gbps connections up to 3 meters over OM3 multimode fiber (MMF). Each end integrates four parallel transceivers, each operating at 50Gbps. Fully compliant with IEEE 802.3, SFF-8665, SFF-8636, and QSFP56 MSA standards, this plug-and-play AOC offers a cost-effective and reliable solution for data centers and high-speed interconnect applications.

title: Single-mode LC/UPC Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra | Low Insertion Loss 0.1dB | Optimized for Hi-Res Audio Streaming (Copy)
descriptionHtml:
🔊 A Trusted Choice in the Audiophile Community

This single-mode LC/UPC to LC/UPC fiber patch cable by SpeedyFiberTX, featuring Corning® SMF-28® Ultra fiber, has become a popular upgrade option across audio forums in recent years.

Whether for two-channel streaming setups, digital streaming DACs, or high-end audio network switches, this cable integrates seamlessly.

Tested by audiophiles from Taiwan and around the world, it consistently delivers low noise, high signal clarity, and stable soundstage, even without special tuning or wrapping. It’s often regarded as the best price-performance option among entry-level single-mode optical cables.

Recommended Pairing

For best results, pair with the SpeedyFiberTX Audio-Optimized SFP Module (SFP1G-LX-31-AF). This combo has been field-tested in Hi-Fi setups to provide optimal signal integrity from NAS to DAC through audio-grade switches.

title: 10GBASE-LR SFP+ Industrial Transceiver Module | 1310nm 20km LC DOM
descriptionHtml:
10GBASE-LR SFP+ Transceiver Module (SMF, 1310nm, 20km, LC, Industrial, DOM)

This SFP+ transceiver supports up to 20km link lengths over LC duplex SMF fiber. This transceiver is compliant with SFF-8431, SFF-8432 and IEEE 802.3ae standards.

Digital diagnostics monitoring is available via a 2-wire serial interface, as specified in SFF-8472. Featuring an operating temperature range of -40°C to 85°C, this industrial fiber optic transceiver can work in harsh industrial environments.

seo.description: SpeedyFiberTX 10GBASE-LR industrial SFP+ transceiver supports 20km over OS2 SMF via LC duplex connector at 1310nm. Cisco SFP-10G-LR-I compatible, with DOM and -40°C to 85°C temp range, it’s ideal for telecom, industrial Ethernet, and outdoor networking.

title: UltraX 19”1U Enclosure for Fusion Splicing, Fixed Type
descriptionHtml: SpeedyFiberTX UltraX 1U enclosure is a rack mountable interconnect point specifically designed to manage dense fiber applications. This enclosure offers management of density up to 144 fibers. The detachable adapter plate on module cassette can be either installed indepently and used along with fusion splicing kits. The detachable front cabling rack is designed with reliable hinge structure for friendly future maintenance.

seo.description: SpeedyFiberTX UltraX 19吋 1U 熔接型光纖收容箱（固定式）專為高密度光纖應用設計，可機架安裝並支援最多 144 芯光纖管理。配備可拆式模組化轉接板，可搭配熔接套件靈活部署。前端走線架採用鉸鏈結構，提升維護便利性與可靠性。非常適合需要高密度光纖管理與機架式解決方案的資料中心與電信網路。

title: UltraN HD 19”1U Enclosure with 4 x Module Cassette or 4 x Adapter Panel, Sliding Type
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX UltraN 1U Rack Mount Fiber Enclosure (compatible with cassettes and adapter panels, sliding type) is designed to house up to four Ultra Family MPO/MTP® module cassettes or fiber adapter panels, providing a flexible and modular solution for diverse fiber optic patching and termination needs. Its sliding tray design ensures easy front access to fiber connections, making it an ideal choice for backbone cabling, distribution, or cross-connect applications in both main and horizontal distribution areas.

When combined with MDC-MPO/MTP® or SN-MPO/MTP® module cassettes or adapter panels from the SpeedyFiberTX Ultra family, the enclosure can support a patching density of up to 256 fibers within a 1U space.

UltraN is available in two versions, with front panel designs that accommodate either plastic or metal cassettes and adapter panels, ensuring broad compatibility. Version A for metal adapter panels and cassettes, and version B for plastic adapter panels and cassettes.

title: UltraX HD 19”1U Enclosure with 4 x Module Cassette or 4 x Adapter Panel, Fixed Type
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX UltraX 1U Rack Mount Fiber Enclosure (Fixed Type) is expertly designed to accommodate up to four Ultra family MPO/MTP® module cassettes or fiber adapter panels, delivering a modular and versatile solution for a wide range of fiber optic patching and termination needs. The enclosure features easy front access to fiber connections, making it ideal for transitioning from backbone cabling to distribution, connecting to active equipment, or serving as a cross-connect in both main and horizontal distribution areas.

When paired with MDC-MPO/MTP® or SN-MPO/MTP® module cassettes or adapter panels from the SpeedyFiberTX Ultra family, the enclosure can achieve a patching density of up to 256 fibers within a 1U space.

The UltraX comes in two versions: version A for metal adapter panels and cassettes, and version B for plastic adapter panels and cassettes.

UltraN is available in two versions, with front panel designs that accommodate either plastic or metal cassettes and adapter panels, ensuring broad compatibility. Version A for metal adapter panels and cassettes, and version B for plastic adapter panels and cassettes.

seo.description: 100GBASE QSFP28 工業級主動光纖線（AOC）是一款四通道可插拔光纖組件，專為高效能短距離互連而設計。此線材在 850nm 波長多模光纖（MMF）上運行，每個方向整合四條數據通道，提供總頻寬 100Gbps。採用 38 針腳邊緣連接器，完全符合 QSFP28 MSA 標準。非常適合應用於資料中心、Infiniband FDR/EDR 系統，以及需要穩定高速連線的工業環境。

Featured by replaceable front adapter panels, the series facilitate system upgrading and maintenance, and cut construction cost.

seo.description: SpeedyFiberTX PSP PLC 分路器光纖收容箱是一款 19 吋 1U 機架式解決方案，專為需要比 PSB 系列更大進出線容量的 PLC 分光器設計。採用長轉接板結構與可更換前端轉接板，PSP 提供充足的安裝空間，並方便系統升級與維護，有效降低施工成本。作為 PSB 系列的全方位延伸版本，PSP 適合應用於電信與資料中心等高容量光纖配線場景。

title: Signal Fire AI-9 Fiber Fusion Splicer (6 Motor Core Alignment)
descriptionHtml:
Signal Fire – The Best-Selling Budget Splicer


Faster Splicing & Heating 
The AI-9 fusion splicing machine uses a powerful high-speed motor that allows fast 5S splice and 15S heat, continuous splice and heats about 260 times. The UPGRADED TRANSPARENT HEATING SLOT has the function of heating part automatic lid closing, also it is compatible with SC fiber optic. Newly added cooling disc facilitates the simultaneous fusion of multiple sets of optical fibers.

Built-In Power Meter & VFL
Using the core alignment technology which is more precise and less splicing loss. Effectively measure connection loss,verify continuity and help assess fiber link transmission quality. OPM can be switched between six states, wavelength of 850nm， 1300nm,1310nm,1490nm,1550nm,1625nm. VFL can be switched between three states, power: 15mW, 2Hz flashing and steady on mode.

3-in-1 Fiber Holder
3 In 1 Fiber Holder suit for single-mode fiber (SMF/G 652), BIF/G.657); Suitable for single mode, multi-mode, bare fiber, tail fiber, skin fber, jumper, invisible fiber fusion; Splice Loss: 0.02dB (SM),0.01dB (MM),0. 04dB (DS/NZDS). The cladding diameter 80-150μm.

Clear LCD & Long Time Standby
With 5-inch high resolution screen, it is up to 300 times the focus magnifications when X/Y Axis displayed separately, 150 times focused magnifications when X/Y Axis displayed simultaneously. 7800 mAh high-capacity lithium battery charging ≤ 3.5 hours.

Intelligent Interaction
This splicing heating machine can be connected to mobile app, ten different languages can be switched like English, French, Russia, Italian, Portuguese, polish, Spanish, Thai, Arabic which is convenient for customers to use. You can check the data by your mobile phone and downloaded or output at any time, also the splicing records can be stored”

title: Signal Fire AI-5 Fiber Fusion Splicer (4 Motors Core Alignment)
descriptionHtml:
Signal Fire – The Best-Selling Budget Splicer


Faster Splicing & Heating
The AI-5 fusion splicing machine uses a four-motor core alignment system that allows fast 8s splice time and 18s heat time, supporting about 160 splice/heat cycles per charge. Efficient performance helps save engineers’ working time.

Core Alignment Technology
Equipped with advanced core/cladding alignment and real-time ARC calibration, providing more precise splicing with lower splice loss compared to cladding-only alignment. Typical splice loss: 0.02 dB (SM), 0.01 dB (MM), 0.04 dB (DS/NZDS).

3-in-1 Fiber Holder
The versatile fiber holder supports SM (G.652 & G.657), MM (G.651), DS (G.657), NZDS (G.655), as well as bare fiber, pigtail, jumper, and drop cable. Cladding diameter range: 80–150 μm.

Clear LCD & Long Battery Life
Features a 5-inch TFT high-resolution display, providing 320× magnification (X or Y single display) and 160× magnification (X+Y dual display). Built-in 5200 mAh high-capacity lithium battery, charging time ≤ 3.5 hours, supports about 160 splice/heat cycles.

Intelligent Interaction
Supports Bluetooth 4.2 connection with mobile APP, enabling data synchronization and cloud storage. The USB port can charge mobile devices such as smartphones, making field work more convenient.
