title: 400G QSFP-DD AOC
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX 400G QSFP-DD AOC

The 400G QSFP-DD active optical cables are designed for use in 400 Gigabit Ethernet links over OM4 multimode fibers, and contain eight multi-mode fibers (MMF) optic transceivers per end, each operating at data rates of up to 53Gb/s. This active optical cable is compliant with IEEE 802.3cd, OIF-CEI-04.0, QSFP-DD MSA, and QSFP-DD-CMIS-rev4p0.

Thin and lightweight AOC cables simplify cable management, enabling an efficient system airflow, which is critical in high-density racks. It is used extensively in cloud and supercomputers due to its low cost, high-value proposition, and increased reliability.

seo.description: The 400G QSFP-DD Active Optical Cable (AOC) is designed for 400Gbps Ethernet links over OM4 multimode fiber (MMF), supporting distances up to 10 meters. Each end integrates eight parallel MMF transceivers, each operating at 53Gbps, delivering high bandwidth with low latency. Fully compliant with IEEE 802.3cd, OIF-CEI-04.0, QSFP-DD MSA, and CMIS standards, this lightweight and hot-swappable AOC simplifies cable management and enhances airflow in high-density racks. Ideal for cloud computing, hyperscale data centers, and supercomputing environments that require reliable high-speed interconnects.

title: 200G QSFP56 AOC, Armored
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX 200G QSFP56 AOC, Armored

This is a Four-Channels, Pluggable, Parallel, Fiber-Optic QSFP56 for 200 Gigabit Ethernet Applications.

This transceiver is a high performance module for short-range multi-lane data communication and interconnection applications. It integrates four data lanes in each direction.

seo.description: The 200G QSFP56 Armored Active Optical Cable (AOC) is a high-performance fiber assembly designed for robust and short-range multi-lane interconnects. It integrates four data lanes in each direction, delivering 200Gbps total bandwidth over multimode fiber (MMF) at 850nm. With its armored design, it provides enhanced durability for industrial environments while remaining fully compliant with QSFP56 MSA, IEEE 802.3, SFF-8665, and SFF-8636 standards. Ideal for data centers, high-performance computing, and telecom applications requiring reliable and protected high-speed connections.

title: 50G SFP56 AOC, Armored
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX 50G SFP56 AOC, Armored

SFP56 Active Optical Cables are direct-attach fiber assemblies with SFP56 connectors. They are suitable for very short distances and offer a cost-effective way to connect within racks and across adjacent racks. The module is a Single-Channel, Pluggable, Fiber-Optic SFP56 for 50 Gigabit Ethernet and Infiniband EDR Applications.

This module is designed to operate over multimode fiber systems using a nominal wavelength of 850nm. The electrical interface uses a 20 contact edge type connector.

seo.description: The 50G SFP56 Armored Active Optical Cable provides a robust and cost-effective interconnect for 50Gbps Ethernet and Infiniband EDR applications. With durable armored protection, it is ideal for short-distance connections within racks and across adjacent racks in high-performance data centers. Built with multimode fiber and SFP56 connectors, it ensures high reliability and low maintenance.

title: 400G QSFP-DD AOC, Armored
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX 400G QSFP-DD Active Optical Cable, Armored

This is an 8-channel pluggable parallel fiber-optic QSFP-DD Active Optical Cable (AOC) designed for high-performance short-reach data communication and interconnect applications.

It provides an aggregate data rate of 400Gbps using eight lanes in each direction, each operating at 53.125Gbps PAM4.

With Forward Error Correction (FEC), the module supports transmission distances up to 70m over OM3 and 100m over OM4 multimode fiber.

It adopts 850nm VCSEL transmitters and PIN photodiode receivers, and features a 76-pin edge connector compliant with the QSFP-DD MSA for reliable electrical and optical performance.

seo.description: The 400G QSFP-DD Armored Active Optical Cable (AOC) delivers reliable 400Gbps Ethernet performance for next-generation data centers and telecom environments. It integrates eight 53.125Gbps PAM4 lanes per direction over multimode fiber (MMF) using 850nm VCSEL transmitters and PIN photodetectors. With distances up to 70m on OM3 and 100m on OM4, the armored construction ensures exceptional durability and signal integrity. Featuring a 76-pin QSFP-DD edge connector, this AOC provides high-speed, low-latency, and robust interconnects ideal for HPC, cloud, and industrial applications.

title: TAA Compliant | 12-Fiber Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO/UPC to Non-Pinned MPO/UPC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM3 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type B, Aqua MPO Connectors, Aqua Cable Jacket | OFNP Jacket
descriptionHtml:
TAA Compliant | 12-Fiber Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO/UPC to Non-Pinned MPO/UPC Jumper | Corning® ClearCurve® OM3 Multimode Optical Fiber | Type B, Aqua MPO Connectors, Aqua Cable Jacket | OFNP Jacket

This MPO to MPO jumper enables seamless migration to higher data rates when used with trunk cables, making it ideal for high-density fiber patching within cabinets. Featuring non-pinned UPC connectors with Type B polarity and built with Corning® ClearCurve® OM3 fiber, it offers low insertion loss, high return loss, and reliable performance. Pre-terminated for easy plug-and-play deployment, this cost-effective solution supports 40G/100G multimode transceivers in data center, FTTH, and EPON environments, TAA Compliant.

seo.description: Low Loss Non-Pinned MPO UPC to Non-Pinned MPO UPC Jumper features Corning® ClearCurve® OM3 Multimode Fiber with Type B polarity and a pre-terminated design for consistent low-loss performance. Featuring non-pinned aqua MPO connectors and an aqua jacket, it supports high-density patching and 40GBASE-SR4/100GBASE-SR4 multimode parallel optics in modern data centers.

title: 12 Fibers MPO Female Low Loss Single-mode Loopback Module
descriptionHtml:
12 MPO Fibers Female Single-mode Loopback Module

MPO loopback modules are used widely within testing environment especially within parallel optics 40/100G networks. Devices allow verification and testing of transceivers featuring MPO/MTP® interface – 40G PLR4 or 100G PSM4 devices. Loopbacks are built to link Transmitter (TX) and Receivers (RX) positions of MPO/MTP® transceivers interfaces. MPO loopbacks can facilitate and speed up IL testing of optical networks segments by connecting them to MPO/MTP® trunks/patch leads.

seo.description: 12 Fibers MPO Female 9/125 Single-mode Fiber Loopback Module with US Conec MPO connector, low insertion loss ≤1.5dB, and high return loss >50dB. Perfect for 40G/100G MPO/MPO transceiver testing and network troubleshooting in data centers.

title: 16-Fiber Non-Pinned MMC-16 to Non-Pinned MMC-16 Jumper Cable | Corning® SMF-28® Ultra Single-mode Optical Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | Type B, Yellow Cable Jacket | OFNR Jacket
descriptionHtml:
16-Fiber Non-Pinned MMC-16 to Non-Pinned MMC-16 Jumper Cable | Corning® SMF-28® Ultra Single-mode Optical Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | Type B, Yellow Cable Jacket | OFNR Jacket

MMC connectors are designed to support higher fiber counts, the MMC system simplifies capacity upgrades for high-performance applications like hyperscale data centers. The compact form factor delivers up to three times the fiber density per rack unit when compared to MPO/MTP connectors. Providing higher cabling port density and low-loss performance in a compact design to support high-bandwidth applications.

seo.description: High-density 16-Fiber MMC jumper cable with Corning® SMF-28® Ultra singlemode optical fiber. Non-pinned MMC-16 connectors, Type B polarity, OFNR jacket, and low-loss performance. Ideal for OS1/OS2 40G/100G/400G data center, telecom, and hyperscale applications.

title: 0.2dB Single-mode MDC/APC to MDC/APC Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | LSZH Jacket
descriptionHtml:
0.2dB Single-mode MDC/APC to MDC/APC Fiber Patch Cable | Corning SMF-28 Ultra Fiber | OS1/OS2 Compatible | LSZH Jacket

The MDC duplex patch cord is designed for cross-connection between patch panels or distribution boxes and optical fiber equipment. Featuring a compact form factor, push-pull boot, and easy polarity change, MDC connectors enable efficient and flexible deployment. These patch cords are also compatible with SFP-DD transceivers for direct connections.

Available in single-mode (OS2) and multimode (OM3, OM4, OM5) options, including bend-insensitive G.657.A fiber, hybrid versions with standard single-fiber connectors are also offered.

seo.description: High-performance 0.2 dB single-mode MDC/APC to MDC/APC duplex fiber patch cable built with Corning® SMF-28® Ultra fiber for OS1/OS2 networks. LSZH jacket for safe indoor deployment.

title: 200GBASE-SR4 QSFP56 850nm 100m DOM MPO-12/UPC MMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
The 200GBASE-SR4 QSFP56 optical transceiver is a 4-channel, hot-pluggable module designed for short-reach 200GbE applications over multimode fiber.

Each lane operates at 53.125Gb/s PAM4, providing an aggregate data rate of 200Gb/s.

This module uses an 850nm VCSEL laser array and PIN photodiode receiver array to ensure stable optical performance and low bit-error rate (BER).

It supports transmission distances of up to 70m on OM3 and 100m on OM4 multimode fiber through an MPO-12 UPC connector.

Compliant with IEEE802.3bs 200GBASE-SR4 and CMIS4.0, the transceiver features digital diagnostic monitoring (DDM/DOM) via the I²C interface for real-time performance tracking and interoperability with major switch platforms.

It is an ideal solution for high-density data center interconnects, switch-to-server links, and high-performance computing (HPC) networks.

seo.description: High-performance 200GBASE-SR4 QSFP56 optical transceiver module, compliant with IEEE 802.3bs. Supports up to 212Gbps transmission over multimode fiber, with maximum reach of 70m on OM3 and 100m on OM4. Features 4×53Gbps PAM4 VCSEL transmitters, PIN receivers, MPO-12 interface, ≤5.5W low power consumption, PAM4 modulation, and hot-pluggable QSFP56 form factor. Ideal for short-reach data centers and high-density 200G Ethernet interconnects.

title: 200GBASE-FR4 QSFP56 1310nm 2km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
The 200GBASE-FR4 QSFP56 optical transceiver is a hot-pluggable module designed for 200 Gigabit Ethernet applications over single-mode fiber (SMF) up to 2 km.

It integrates four lanes of 50 Gb/s PAM4 signals for an aggregate data rate of 200 Gb/s. Each lane uses a CWDM wavelength (1271 nm, 1291 nm, 1311 nm, 1331 nm) and employs an EML transmitter and PIN receiver with DSP for enhanced signal integrity and low power operation.

The module is compliant with IEEE 802.3bs 200GBASE-FR4 and CMIS 4.0 standards and provides digital diagnostic monitoring (DDM/DOM) via the I²C interface.

It is an ideal solution for data centers and telecommunication networks requiring reliable long-reach 200 G optical links.

seo.description: High-performance 200G QSFP56 CWDM4 optical transceiver module, compliant with IEEE 802.3bs. Supports up to 212Gbps transmission over single-mode fiber with maximum reach of 2 km. Features 4×50Gb/s PAM4 CWDM channels (1271, 1291, 1311, 1331 nm), LC duplex interface, ≤6.5W power consumption, PAM4 modulation, and hot-pluggable QSFP56 form factor. Ideal for 200G Ethernet interconnects, data center links, and metro network applications.

title: 200GBASE-LR4 QSFP56 1310nm 10km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
The 200GBASE-LR4 QSFP56 optical transceiver is a hot-pluggable module designed for 200 Gigabit Ethernet applications over single-mode fiber (SMF) up to 10km. It integrates four lanes of 50Gb/s PAM4 signals for an aggregate data rate of 200Gb/s. Each lane uses a LAN-WDM wavelength (1271nm, 1291nm, 1311nm, 1331nm) and employs a cooled EA-DFB laser with PIN receiver and low-noise TIA for superior signal integrity.

The module complies with IEEE 802.3bs 200GBASE-LR4 and CMIS 4.0 standards, and supports digital diagnostic monitoring via the I²C interface. It is ideal for data-center inter-rack connections, telecom aggregation links, and long-reach high-capacity networks requiring stable 200G optical performance.

seo.description: High-performance 200GBASE-LR4 QSFP56 optical transceiver module, compliant with IEEE 802.3bs. Supports 200G Ethernet links up to 10 km over SMF using LAN-WDM wavelengths (1295.56, 1300.05, 1304.58, 1309.14 nm). Features cooled EA-DFB EML transmitters, PIN receivers, duplex LC interface, ≤8W power consumption, PAM4 modulation, CMIS 4.0 management, and hot-pluggable QSFP56 form factor. Ideal for data center interconnects, metro networks, and long-reach 200G Ethernet applications.

title: 400GBASE-DR4 OSFP Finned Top PAM4 1310nm 500m DOM MPO-12/APC SMF Optical Transceiver Module, Breakout to 4 x 100G-DR
descriptionHtml:
The 400GBASE-DR4 OSFP Finned Top optical transceiver is a high-performance module designed for short to medium-reach 400GbE applications over single-mode fiber (SMF).

It supports four parallel lanes of 106.25Gb/s PAM4 for an aggregate bandwidth of 400Gb/s.

Operating at 1310nm, the module uses integrated EML transmitters and PIN photodiodes to achieve up to 500m transmission with FEC.

It features an MPO-12/APC connector, compliant with IEEE802.3bs 400GBASE-DR4, OSFP MSA, and CMIS4.0 standards.

The Finned Top housing enhances thermal performance for data center and AI cluster environments, supporting breakout to 4×100G-DR channels for flexible network deployment.

seo.description: High-performance 400G OSFP DR4 transceiver module, supporting 425Gbps data rate over 500m single mode fiber (SMF) with MPO-12 connector. Featuring DFB transmitter, PIN receiver, PAM4 modulation, and ≤12W power consumption. Ideal for hyperscale data centers and high-speed Ethernet networks.

title: 400GBASE-SR8 OSFP Finned Top PAM4 850nm 100m DOM MPO-16/APC MMF Optical Transceiver Module, Breakout to 2×200G-SR4
descriptionHtml:
The 400GBASE-SR8 OSFP Finned Top optical transceiver is a high-performance module designed for short-reach 400GbE applications over multimode fiber (MMF).

It supports eight parallel lanes of 53.125Gb/s PAM4 for an aggregate data rate of 400Gb/s.

Operating at 850nm, it uses a VCSEL laser array and PIN photo-detector array to achieve up to 70m on OM3 and 100m on OM4 fiber.

The module features an MPO-16 APC or dual MTP-12 APC connector, and complies with IEEE802.3cm 400GBASE-SR8 and OSFP MSA standards.

The finned-top housing provides enhanced thermal management, making it ideal for AI clusters, HPC networks, and high-density data centers with breakout support to 2×200G-SR4.

seo.description: High-performance 400G OSFP SR8 transceiver with 8×53.125Gbps PAM4 lanes, VCSEL transmitter, PIN receiver, MPO16/2×MPO12 APC connectors, supporting up to 100m over OM4 multimode fiber. Optimized for short-range 400G Ethernet data center interconnects.

title: 400GBASE-FR4 QSFP-DD PAM4 1310nm 2km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
The 400GBASE-FR4 QSFP-DD optical transceiver is a high-performance module designed for 400GbE single-mode applications up to 2km.

It integrates 4 CWDM optical lanes, each operating at 106.25Gb/s PAM4, for an aggregate data rate of 400Gb/s. The central wavelengths are 1271nm, 1291nm, 1311nm, and 1331nm, compliant with the ITU-T G.694.2 CWDM grid.

The module features a Duplex LC/UPC connector, supporting IEEE 802.3cu 400GBASE-FR4, QSFP-DD MSA, and 100G Lambda MSA standards.

Digital diagnostics are accessible via the I²C CMIS interface, offering a compact and power-efficient solution for data center and cloud backbone networks.

seo.description: High-performance 400G QSFP-DD FR4 optical transceiver module, supporting up to 2km transmission over SMF with duplex LC connector. Features 4 CWDM lanes (1271, 1291, 1311, 1331nm), PAM4 modulation, ≤10W power consumption, and advanced EML transmitters with PIN receivers. Ideal for 400G Ethernet applications requiring reliable and efficient optical communication.

title: 400GBASE-SR8 QSFP-DD PAM4 850nm 70m@OM3 / 100m@OM4 DOM MPO-24 MMF Optical Transceiver Module, Breakout to 2 × 200G-SR4 and 8 × 50G-SR
descriptionHtml:
The 400GBASE-SR8 QSFP-DD optical transceiver is a high-performance, short-reach module designed for 400GbE, 200GbE SR4 breakout, and 8×50GbE SR applications over multimode fiber (MMF).

It supports 8 parallel lanes of 53.125 Gb/s PAM4, providing an aggregate bandwidth of 400 Gb/s.

Operating at 850 nm, the module uses a VCSEL laser array and PIN photo-detector array to achieve up to 70 m on OM3 and 100 m on OM4 fiber.

It complies with IEEE 802.3cm 400GBASE-SR8 and QSFP-DD MSA, featuring digital diagnostics via I²C.

The MPO-24 connector supports direct 400G links or breakout to 2×200G SR4 or 8×50G SR channels, making it ideal for AI clusters and high-density data centers.

seo.description: High-performance 400G QSFP-DD SR8 optical transceiver module with 8x53Gbps VCSEL transmitters and PIN receivers. Supports 400Gbps Ethernet up to 70m on OM3 MMF or 100m on OM4 MMF via MPO-24 connector. Hot-pluggable, low power consumption ≤12W, compliant with IEEE 802.3cd standard.

title: 400GBASE-SR4 OSFP Flat Top PAM4 850nm 50m DOM MPO-12/APC MMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
The 400GBASE-SR4 OSFP Flat Top optical transceiver is a high-performance, hot-pluggable module designed for short-reach 400GbE applications over multimode fiber (MMF).

It supports four parallel channels of 106.25Gb/s PAM4 for an aggregate data rate of 400Gb/s.

Operating at 850nm, it uses a VCSEL laser array and PIN photodiode array, achieving link distances up to 30m over OM3 and 50m over OM4 fiber.

The module adopts an MPO-12/APC connector and complies with IEEE802.3db and OSFP MSA, supporting digital diagnostics via the I²C interface.

It is ideal for high-density 400G Ethernet, AI clusters, and top-of-rack interconnects in data centers.

seo.description: High-performance 400G OSFP SR4 optical transceiver module, compliant with IEEE 802.3cd. Supports up to 424Gbps transmission over multimode fiber with maximum reach of 30m on OM3 and 50m on OM4. Features 4×106Gbps PAM4 VCSEL transmitters, PIN receivers, MPO-12 interface, ≤14W power consumption, PAM4 modulation, and hot-pluggable OSFP form factor. Ideal for short-reach 400G Ethernet interconnects and high-density data center applications.

title: 400GBASE-ER8 QSFP-DD PAM4 1310nm 40km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
The 400GBASE-ER8 QSFP-DD optical transceiver is a high-performance module designed for 400GbE long-haul applications up to 40km over single-mode fiber (SMF).

It converts 8×53.125Gb/s (PAM4) electrical inputs into 8 LWDM optical channels multiplexed within the 1310nm band (1264.5–1337.5nm) for an aggregate data rate of 400Gb/s.

On the receiver side, the module demultiplexes the 8 optical channels and converts them back to 8 PAM4 electrical outputs.

Compliant with IEEE 802.3cn 400GBASE-ER8, QSFP-DD MSA HW Rev 5.0, and CMIS 4.0, it supports digital diagnostics via the I²C interface and is optimized for carrier-grade and data center backbone networks.

seo.description: High-performance 400G QSFP-DD ER8 optical transceiver module, supporting up to 40km transmission over single mode fiber (SMF) with duplex LC connector. Features 8 LWDM lanes, PAM4 modulation, ≤14W power consumption, advanced EML transmitters and APD receivers. Fully compliant with IEEE 802.3cn and QSFP-DD MSA standards, ideal for data centers and long-haul 400G Ethernet backbone networks.

title: 400GBASE-DR4 QSFP-DD PAM4 1310nm 500m DOM MPO-12/APC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
The 400GBASE-DR4 QSFP-DD optical transceiver is designed for high-performance 400GbE data center and backbone applications over single-mode fiber (SMF) up to 500m.

It converts 8×53.125Gb/s (PAM4) electrical signals into 4 parallel optical channels, each operating at 100Gb/s, to achieve an aggregate 400Gb/s data rate.

On the receiver side, it converts 4 optical lanes of 100Gb/s each back into 8 electrical lanes of 50Gb/s (PAM4).

Operating at 1310nm, the module adopts an MPO-12/APC connector for optical interface and a QSFP-DD MSA-compliant edge connector for electrical interface.

Compliant with IEEE802.3bs 400GBASE-DR4, it supports DOM/diagnostic monitoring via I²C, enabling precise link monitoring and optimized performance for large-scale deployments.

seo.description: High-performance 400G QSFP-DD DR4 optical transceiver module for up to 500m transmission over SMF with MPO-12 connector. Supports 8x53.125Gbps PAM4 lanes, compliant with IEEE 802.3bs and QSFP-DD MSA. Ideal for hyperscale data centers and 400G Ethernet interconnects.

title: 400GBASE-LR4 QSFP-DD PAM4 1310nm 10km DOM Duplex LC/UPC SMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
The 400GBASE-LR4 QSFP-DD optical transceiver is a high-performance module designed for 400GbE long-reach applications up to 10km over single-mode fiber (SMF).

It integrates 8×53.125Gb/s (PAM4) electrical lanes into 4 CWDM optical lanes of 106.25Gb/s each, multiplexed and demultiplexed for 400Gb/s aggregate data transmission.

Operating at central wavelengths of 1271nm, 1291nm, 1311nm, and 1331nm as defined in ITU-T G.694.2, this module uses a duplex LC connector and requires host FEC to achieve 10km reach. Compliant with IEEE802.3bs, 100GLambda MSA 400G-LR4, and QSFP-DD MSA, it supports digital diagnostics (DDM/DOM) via the I²C interface and is optimized for high-density data center and telecom backbone networks.

seo.description: High-performance 400G QSFP-DD LR4 optical transceiver module, supporting up to 10km transmission over single mode fiber (SMF) with duplex LC connector. Features 4 CWDM lanes (1271, 1291, 1311, 1331nm), PAM4 modulation, ≤10W power consumption, and advanced EML transmitters with PIN receivers. Compliant with 400G-LR4-10 MSA, ideal for data centers and high-capacity optical networks.

title: 400GBASE-SR4 QSFP112 PAM4 850nm 50m DOM MPO-12/APC MMF Optical Transceiver Module
descriptionHtml:
The 400GBASE-SR4 QSFP112 optical transceiver is a 4-channel, hot-pluggable module designed for short-reach 400GbE applications over multimode fiber. Each lane operates at 106.25 Gb/s PAM4, delivering an aggregate data rate of 400Gb/s.

It uses an 850nm VCSEL laser array and PIN photodiode receiver array to support transmission up to 30m over OM3 and 50m over OM4 MMF through an MPO-12 APC connector.

Compliant with IEEE 802.3db and CMIS 4.0 standards, this transceiver supports DOM via the I²C interface and is ideal for high-density data-center interconnects or 4 × 100G breakout applications in next-generation Ethernet networks.

seo.description: The 400G QSFP112 SR4 optical transceiver (TSQM4-NAAMA1C) is designed for short-reach Ethernet applications over multimode fiber (MMF). It supports up to 424Gbps with PAM4 modulation, operating at 850nm VCSEL and PIN receiver technology. With MPO12 APC connectors, low power consumption ≤14W, and up to 50m transmission over OM4 fiber, it is ideal for data centers and high-bandwidth interconnects.

title: 50G SFP56 AOC
descriptionHtml:
SpeedyFiberTX 50G SFP56 AOC

SFP56 Active Optical Cables are direct-attach fiber assemblies with SFP56 connectors. They are suitable for very short distances and offer a cost-effective way to connect within racks and across adjacent racks.

The module is a Single-Channel, Pluggable, Fiber-Optic SFP56 for 50 Gigabit Ethernet and Infiniband EDR Applications. This module is designed to operate over multimode fiber systems using a nominal wavelength of 850nm. The electrical interface uses a 20 contact edge type connector.

seo.description: The 50G SFP56 Active Optical Cable (AOC) is a direct-attach fiber assembly with SFP56 connectors, designed for short-distance 50Gbps connections over multimode fiber (MMF). Operating at 850nm, this single-channel pluggable fiber module offers a cost-effective solution compared to discrete transceivers and patch cables. Fully compliant with SFP56 MSA standards, it is ideal for 50G Ethernet, Infiniband EDR, and high-speed data center interconnect applications.

title: 100GBASE-PSM4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module , 1310nm 2km, DOM Monitoring , MPO-12/APC Interface, Breakout to 4 × 25G-LR
descriptionHtml:
100GBASE-PSM4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module , 1310nm 2km, DOM Monitoring , MPO-12/APC Interface, Breakout to 4 × 25G-LR (Cisco QSFP-100G-PSM4-S Compatible)

This product is a Four-Channel, Pluggable, Parallel, Fiber-Optic QSFP28 Transceiver for 100G Ethernet Applications.

The QSFP28 full-duplex optical module offers 4 independent transmit and receive channels, each capable of 26Gbps operation for an aggregate data rate of 104Gbps 2km using single mode fiber. These modules are designed to operate over single mode fiber systems using 1310nm DFB laser array. An optical fiber ribbon cable with an MPO/MTPTM connector can be plugged into the QSFP28 module receptacle.

QSFP28 PSM4 is one kind of parallel transceiver which provides increased port density and total system cost savings.

seo.description: This 100G QSFP28 PSM4 optical transceiver from SpeedyFiberTX supports 2km reach over single-mode fiber (SMF) using 1310nm wavelength, with MPO-12 connector and power consumption under 3.5W. Ideal for data centres, 100G Ethernet and high-speed parallel links.

title: 100GBASE-LR4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module, 1310nm 10km, DOM Monitoring, LC-UPC Interface, OTU4-Compatible
descriptionHtml:
100GBASE-LR4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module, 1310nm 10km, DOM Monitoring, LC-UPC Interface, OTU4-Compatible

This product is a 100Gb/s transceiver module designed for optical communication applications compliant to OTU4 4I1-9D1F requirements specified in ITU-T Recommendations G.959.1/G.709 and Supplement 39(G.sup39). The module converts 4 input channels of 28Gb/s electrical data to 4 channels of LAN WDM optical signals and then multiplexes them into a single channel for 100Gb/s optical transmission. title: 100GBASE-LR4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module, 1310nm 10km SMF, DOM Monitoring, LC-UPC Interface
descriptionHtml:
100GBASE-LR4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module, 1310nm 10km SMF, DOM Monitoring, LC-UPC Interface (Cisco QSFP-100G-LR4-S Compatible)T

his product is a 100Gb/s transceiver module designed for optical communication applications compliant to 100GBASE-LR4 of the IEEE P802.3ba standard. The module converts 4 input channels of 25Gb/s electrical data to 4 channels of LAN WDM optical signals and then multiplexes them into a single channel for 100Gb/s optical transmission. Reversely on the receiver side, the module de-multiplexes a 100Gb/s optical input into 4 channels of LAN WDM optical signals and then converts them to 4 output channels of electrical data.

The central wavelengths of the 4 LAN WDM channels are 1295.56, 1300.05, 1304.58 and 1309.14 nm as members of the LAN WDM wavelength grid defined in IEEE 802.3ba. The high performance cooled LAN WDM DFB transmitters and high sensitivity PIN receivers provide superior performance for 100Gigabit Ethernet applications up to 10km links and compliant to optical interface with IEEE802.3ba Clause 88 100GBASE-LR4 requirements. title: 100GBASE-CWDM4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module, 1271-1331nm 10km SMF, DOM Monitoring, LC-UPC Interface
descriptionHtml:
100GBASE-CWDM4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module, 1271–1331nm 10km SMF, DOM Monitoring, LC-UPC Interface

The QSFP28 100G-CWDM4-10km module is a highly integrated 4x25G transceiver focused on reach, bandwidth, density and cost for high port-count 100G systems, and client-side 100G interfaces. It is compliant with the 100G 4WDM-10 MSA, which is based on the CWDM4 MSA version 1.1. It is interoperable with CWDM4 transceivers over a 10 km reach.

seo.description: High-performance 100GBASE-CWDM4 QSFP28 transceiver for 10 km single-mode fiber. Supports 1271-1331 nm CWDM wavelengths, LC-UPC interface, and DOM monitoring for reliable data-center & metro applications.

title: 100GBASE-ER4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module, 1310nm LAN-WDM 30km SMF, DOM Monitoring, LC-UPC Interface
descriptionHtml:
100GBASE-ER4 QSFP28 Optical Transceiver Module, 1310nm LAN-WDM 30km SMF, DOM Monitoring, LC-UPC Interface

This product is designed for 30km optical communication applications. This module contains 4-lane optical transmitter, 4-lane optical receiver and module management block including 2 wire serial inter-face. The optical signals are multiplexed to a single-mode fiber through an industry standard LC connector.

The product is designed with form factor, optical/electrical connection and digital diagnostic interface according to the QSFP+ Multi-Source Agreement (MSA). It has been designed to meet the harshest external operating conditions including temperature, humidity and EMI interference.

seo.description: High-capacity 100GBASE-ER4 QSFP28 transceiver up to 30 km over single-mode fiber (G.652). 1310 nm LAN-WDM, LC Duplex, DOM diagnostics, ideal for data centre interconnect.

title: 4-Fiber Industrial Armored LC/UPC to LC/UPC Multimode OM1 Fiber Optic Patch Cable | Ø4.5mm Black Armored Cable | Red & Black LSZH Fanout Tubes
descriptionHtml: The SpeedyFiberTX 4-fiber LC/UPC to LC/UPC armored multimode patch cable is built with OM1 62.5/125μm fiber for reliable short-distance data transmission.
